comment: He  knows the subject very well, and has interesting discussions in class. NO exams or quizzes. Just homework and projects. You can get a good experience in his class , especially working on the project. 12 students in class got  8  - A , 2 - AB , 1 ? B and 1 was only auditing the course
We deserve a better education. Mary is ruining our future. WE DESERVE BETTER!
I am honestly worried about the future of MU Nursing with professor Ross still teaching.

One of the worst profs I've had at MU. I dont understand how she is still teaching. She is going to hurt the reputation of MU Nursing. She is extremely unclear, is degrading to her students, and does not know how to teach. Literally had 5 weeks in a row where she did not actually lecture about content. Hopefully something changes...

Worst professor I've had at MU. Extremely unclear, you never know what her expectations are. She breaks down everyone's confidence and humiliates people in lab. Sends out SO many emails and puts so much on D2L, and none of it helps. You'll get through the class, it's just painful.
Worst prof ever!!! unclear, needless information, and a ridiculous amount of emails a wk. You will work your butt of in her class and get absolutely nothing out of it!!!

So unclear it's not even funny. You never know what she expects from you. She's living in her own world. Send a million e-mails every week... with pointless information. Poor you if you have to take her class.

Is this lady speaking another language? Her teaching style is to break her students down before building them up (and by building them I mean letting them pass) and you learn nothing. She also sends AT LEAST 15 emails a week. Sometimes up to 9 in one day. And believe it or not NONE of them are helpful.
Why is she still teaching!!!???? WORST PROFESSOR I HAVE EVER HAD IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

Worst professor I've had in my life. She's so unclear as to what she wants and sends out 100 e-mails a week with pointless information. She makes everything really complicated and isn't helpful at all when you ask her for help. Lab was fun, but she made it hard and she's very boring in lecture.
Awful professor, hard to follow and picks text questions from nowhere.

Mary is the worst teacher I've ever had at Marquette. She can't teach, she can't write tests/quizzes/emails clearly, and she doesn't answer questions. I was really excited about taking this class, but she ruined it for me. Lab is great and I learned a lot there, but her 2 hr lecture is killer - pointless and painful.

Lab is really interesting in the class, but she is a terrible teacher. She seems in her own world, and does not communicate the necessary information. When I went to her for help, she tried to teach me the same thing 3 times when I told her I understood that portion. She's nice enough, but she is unable to be an effective teacher.

Mary seems like she is a good nurse, but not a good teacher. She knows a lot and is helpful when she is focused, but tends to drift A LOT. She is also not clear about her expectations which is very frustrating. Her tests are pretty good, but definitely require studying. I've had her 2 semesters and she's getting better as time goes on.

Fr. Laurance is a great person who truly means well, but like others have stated already, he is not the greatest teacher. There are no right answers besides his answers. The only discussions he has in class are when he calls on students and even then he's looking for his particular answer. Avoid this man as a teacher if possible.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Father. Laurance. There's so much to say about this man. He is probably my favorite professor at MU, from a personality standpoint. The whole teaching part isn't his brightest quality. He is too knowledgeable for his own good. He often speaks over everyone's head, which makes things confusing. Love the guy, just not as a level 1 theology professor.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Worst class and professor I've had! He is really sweet but isn't the greatest teacher. He will quiz you on things he didn't cover and is all over the place with his lectures. In order to do good you really have to pay close attention even to his side tangents. Also, a very picky grader.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Fr. Laurance is a sweet prof, however it was insanely hard to sit through him talking without falling asleep. He lectures the entire time, and he picks on people randomly during class and tries to get answers out of them for upwards of 5 minutes, which can get uncomfortable. His tests are Bible and lecture based. Overall good guy but boring class.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: He is a very sweet, caring man who is super smart, which sometimes makes the content hard to understand. Very lecture heavy and quite boring at times, but he is very repetitive to ensure you learn the material. As long as you listen and TAKE NOTES, the class is manageable and an easy A, but just long and boring.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Fr. Laurance was the worst theology teacher I've ever had. His lectures are the entire 75 minutes and he makes zero attempt to make the material interesting or even tolerable. We got homework almost every class and the tests were on so much different material it was really difficult to keep track of everything. Strongly recommend against his class

Very passionate and knowledgeable teacher, but I dreaded his class because it was extremely boring. Had a ridiculous 20-25 point curve on his tests, and graded fairly easily on assignments and papers, but having to sit through his 75 minutes classes almost makes it not worth the easiness.

I would never be able to sit through a class with this professor again. Nicest man alive, but he tries to teach way too in depth for an introductory course. I could never stay awake. Easy course with easy assignments, but the tests were hard. I didn't know what I needed to know for the test until he would give us a study guide.

VERY BORING! All you do is sit there and listen. He is too smart for his own good. Nothing he says makes sense and he is no help outside of class. Tests are curved pretty heavily so you don't do too bad.

Laurance is honestly a very nice guy, his lectures can sometimes be boring, bring a drink to keep you awake. very few reflection papers, tests arent bad with provided study guides.   When he draws on the chalkboard though.....he scribbles and draws these enigmas that do not help, but it's no issue anyways, just interesting

Nice professor, but his lectures are a little heavy and hard to follow. Takes questions from homework assignments and makes his tests out of them. Thus his tests are very easy. Don't buy any books, you never turn homework in and you go over each homework assignment as a class. Strict on attendance. One paper, two tests and non-cum'ltve final.

Really nice guy who wants his students to do well. He is so smart though that it is hard for him to mellow it down for us to understand. Talks and moves fast, but not that hard of a grader if you take notes.

He is a very nice guy but class is very very boring. He rambles on and doesn't connect any ideas. He also teaches from a very Catholic stand point, so if you are looking to learn in theology don't take him. Easy class though, barely any work to turn in and huge curve on the tests.

He was an excellent teacher. He is so nice and easy to talk to during office hours. His class is fairly boring but if you pay attention, you will have no problem passing his class! He doesn't give out writing assignments like other theo teachers. The T/F quizzes are easy! As long as you do his study guides and actually read, it's an easy A! :)
Easy class. No papers, only a T/F quiz every week on reading. He is extremely knowledgeable. Gives study guides for tests and curves. Definitely recommend him for Theo 1001!

Fr. Laurance is very passionate about teaching theology. He is a Jesuit priest who graduated from Notre Dame with a PhD. He is extremely smart, but he has trouble "dumbing" down the material for his students. You will have to learn material in this introductory class that you would not have to learn from any other theology professor.
Fr. Laurance is fantastic. A very kind man, and while sometimes he is tough to follow, he is one of the best. He is great!

Fr. Laurance is a nice man, but his lectures in class are very difficult to follow. He has a 6 question true/false quiz on the reading assignment at the beginning of each class, which is fairly easy, but if you are late, you cannot make it up. He curves tests, so they are fairly easy as well.
Average professor for theology, just a basic history class. If you can memorize lectures you will do fine. Also for the writing portion of tests, if you can gauge Oli's opinion you will do well.
ratingTags: BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I took Dr. Oliverio over the summer, and he helped me with my understanding for Theology, but he was very hard, his tests you really need to prepare well for, he usually gives out a study guide, but you need to review the material, he assumes you have a slight background of Theology which I don't'think he should because I had no background.

-90 percent of exam questions come from power points -exam essay question material discussed in class -take good notes, you'll get A's on exams -the pop quizzes are TOUGH but predictable, do the readings -insanely helpful, just be honest about what's going on, he'll help you out big time -attendance plays a big role

Dr. O is a great professor... so understanding and chill and makes a dull class a little more interesting. His lectures can drag but he's so passionate about theology and it shows. Take good notes and do the readings and you'll be fine. Tests are hard but he gives review sheets with everything on the test... so helpful. Take him!

never took theo before, got an A, found the class interesting. very straightforward about what's on tests, just do the study guide. poor time management in lectures but thats about the only con. make sure to do the readings when he starts hinting about quizzes.
Oliverio is an amazing guy! I would take each class with him if I could, you WILL work for your grade.
Tends to poorly manage time, forcing students to cram information towards the end of the course. He's a tough professor and grader but is very helpful in preparing for a second level theology course.

One of the most difficult intro to theology teachers at Marquette. You have to take great notes in class and do all of the textbook reading. His tests are hard and he likes to give quizzes on the readings.

While he is a nice professor, his lectures can get extremely boring. I had trouble staying awake every single class. His exams are difficult and he is a hard grader. He is the only professor that uses the McGrath textbook which is one of the most confusing books you will ever read. I always got straight A's on all papers except in his class.

Do NOT take this guy. He takes pride in saying he is the hardest Theology teacher on campus. Pop quizzes on McGrath, which is an extremely difficult read. Have taken theology since kindergarten, hasn't helped. Fill in the blank tests. Not sure why people said to take this guy. Overall nice guy, but thinks everyone is a theo major

One of the best teachers I've had.  Definitely a class you can't put off though.  Keep up with the readings and his lecture and the class is very straightforward. He is one of the most approachable teachers I've had at this school so far

You're required to read the CHristian Theology textbook by McGrath, which no other theology 1001 professor requires. He knows a lot but he can't teach well. He doesn't give outlines so you just write down everything that comes out of his mouth. He skips around. Sometimes I feel like I'm in an Italian class.

Super nice guy. Definitely take advantage of his office hours. There is a lot of reading, but if you keep up with it, you will do fine. He gave us pop quizzes, but if you read, they're super easy, if you don't, they're super hard.
Really nice guy. Didn't grow up in Catholic school so it was hard for me to grasp the concept. There are easier teachers out there. Tests are pretty difficult and there is a LOT of reading.

This class in really interesting.  Oliverio sometimes goes on rants,but they won't show up on the test so it's ok. Read the book and you will definitely get an A. Without trying at all you should get a B/C or B, the tests are easy.

Tough class for kids who haven't grown up in Catholic school. Go to his office hours right before class and he's very helpful. His grading scale is pretty annoying (3 exams @ 10% each, final is same points but @ 25% of grade).  It's a required class so there's not much you can do but look for an easier professor if you didn't grow up around a bible
Extremely nice guy! Really means well but lectures are very boring!  Have 10 assignments on the readings , a paper, and 3 tests plus a final.

His class is relatively easy. As long as you pay attention to what he says in class, you are good to go for the tests. The tests are easy-theres only 3 plus the final-and only one essay. Class can get very boring, but if you have the will to keep yourself awake you should be fine. Really nice guy and good professor

Dr. Oliverio is a really nice guy and, if you pay attention, his class is an easy A. It can be boring, but if you don't take his class at 8 AM it shouldn't be too difficult to pass. He is also very helpful outside of class if you go to him for help

Ridiculously boring class. His lectures are all over the place and his accent makes him incomprehensible. He makes study guides for the quizzes, midterm and final so you just have to study off that. Got an A, was bored out of my mind and learned nothing.
Dr. Giulea is a very nice man, but he has a very strong accent and is terribly hard to understand. The things gone over in class are usually not even on the quizzes.

Ms. Wilkinson has to be one of the best English professors at Marquette! Her class is very engaging and fun because she likes to talk and make the class laugh.  She is very clear on paper instructions so getting a decent grade on them should not be too difficult.  Too bad she won't be at Marquette next year! Marquette lost a great teacher.

Absolutely loved Ms. Wilkinson! She is super funny, very engaging, young and relate- able. She is very intelligent, and although she is a bit nicer in class than one on one, she is still easy to talk to and makes herself a great resource for your papers. She makes appointments to look over all your papers if you want her to, semi hard grader though

Really nice teacher....always there if you need help and makes sure you know what you are supposed to do for each paper. Class is composed of four papers and the final is a revision of a previous paper. A lot of class discussion and some group work in class but a super easy class.

She is a great professor who loves what she does. She makes class very interesting and tries to get everyone involved. She's a relatively easy grader, especially if you conference with her for papers. Definitely recommend her for ENGL 1001 or 1002.
Really good teacher, class went by real fast and was fun, highly recommend

His tests were 12 questions that were very similar to problems we went thru on his lecture slides. He goes thru a lot of problems to make the homework a little easier. Nice man with funny stories. Very accommodating  and caring of certain situations. The only problem was sometimes the homework and quiz grades brought my overall grade down.
Great teacher and a great man!

Dr. Brown is an awesome teacher!  He really cares about his students and wants to see you succeed. Tests are not easy, but he offers a lot of practice problems that will prepare you if you work through them!

I would definitely recommend Dr. Brown to other students. If you read the book and go into office hours for homework help, an A is easily attainable. He makes the class very entertaining and it's obvious that he cares a lot about his students. He wants everyone to succeed, so put in the effort and your grade will reflect it. Genuinely good person.
I had Dr Brown for physics 1 and 2 and his class was tough but he cares about his students and really is passionate about what he teaches. It's a shame he is retiring! Would recommend to anyone.
Great professor

Dr. Brown was a good choice. He is very intelligent and approachable. Great during office hours. The coursework was manageable if you apply yourself. Can sometimes get off topic, but at least kept students engaged. Would take again.

Dr. Brown was the man! He was a hell of a professor and I really enjoyed going to every one of his lectures. He cared for his students and wanted them to be the best they could be. He made Physics fun. He made sure that every student understood the material in any way he could. Gave plenty of problems in class for help. Would take him again.

First impressions may be deceiving; initially, based on his own description of the course to be "not too bad" and "you should be fine if you read and do the practice problems" I thought that he undermined the difficulty of the course and therefore would teach lethargically. Some days it seemed like he half-taught, but in the end his tests were easy

You'll have to teach yourself. The book is your friend. But his tests are easy and there's no surprises. This class won't make you wanna pull your hair out. He is very open to dropping difficult homework assignments and is a forgiving grader.
fine

Brown is one of the worst professors I've ever had.  Do you know that Aunt you have that never shuts up about pointless stories?  That is Brown.  He goes on rants instead of teaching, and then rants on how students skip class and waste money. He recently posted "answers" to a study guide which included "you should know this" and "this is easy".

Dr. Brown is a great guy who knows his stuff, but often get off topic with unrelated stories that take up a lot of class. If you take him you need to read the book everyday before class otherwise you will be lost in the lecture. The lectures do not cover all the info in the text. Tests are hard. Tutoring Helps A LOT. Homework pts. are key to get A.

Doc. Brown is a good man. If you do the required reading and listen to his lectures an A is not out of reach. He keeps his tests so simple that if you understand the material you can finish in minutes. Likes teaching through anecdotes and stories, which some people don't enjoy but it's a nice break to daunting lectures of other engineering courses.
interesting guy but lectures can be hard to follow, he spends most of the time giving advice and telling stories instead of teaching, he's better if you go to office hours.
Great Professor. I loved going to class and listening to him. He shared an insight into physics that I had never experienced. Take him if you have the chance.
Such a great guy. Heâ??s easy to understand, and pretty funny. Heâ??ll help you whenever you need it, and is more than fair on grading. Takes a tough course and makes it doable!
Nice guy and has some cool stories but is sometimes hard to follow during lecture.

Dr Brown is Very Helpful, Daily reading quiz usually 2 min problem, If the quizes turn out bad he goes over that material more so thats nice. Homework due everyday but go to discussion and its usually done there, labs are ok, only 3 written at home. Books arent horrible but not that helpful either. Fridays usually include funny movies that help.

The class format is different from traditional physics courses, but you'll understand the theory and mathematical processes a whole lot better.  The class is not that bad, and Dr. Brown takes time outside of class to help you if needed

He, and the new physics program, have gotten a *lot* better.  That first semester was a hot mess, but they've worked out the homework, clickers, and tests.  Plus, our section usually has the highest average!  I still hate this book, but it's been streamlined.

Dr. Chavez (now teaching at Saint Martin's University) is the kindest professor I have had thus far. She is so enthusiastic, insightful, and motivating. It's easy to approach her if in need of extra help - she's very sweet. Also, her grading is fair and she gives great feedback on essays. I'm really looking forward to taking more classes with her.
She is really nice and very passionate about literature. I was in her British Literature II class and it was pretty easy, but the readings weren't very interesting.

Every freshman should try to have her as a teacher if they can. She is extremely insightful, teaches material that will matter, and is willing to meet students halfway if they put the work into it. Wonderful teacher=awesome semester.

She is a really great teacher. The class wasn't really difficult and she is a fair grader. If you have any questions she is good about emailing back quick and she is happy to help you! Take her if you get the chance!

Dr. Chavez is wonderful! She's easy to understand and talk to, understanding, sweet, and just a generally wonderful person. I don't feel her grading is particularly hard if you put effort into the assignments. Sorry to hear she isn't teaching 1002 next semester. If you have the opportunity, take a class with her! She's wonderful!!!

I strongly recommend this teacher.  She is one of the most insightful, caring, and intelligent teachers in the honors program.  She will work with you if you are having trouble in class.  Also, she understands that you have other classes, so she will never overload you with work.  Still, you will learn a lot.

I had Dr. Chavez Freshman year for Honors English. Very enthusiastic and interesting. Lots of reading, so try not to fall behind. Be ready for critical analysis and going deeper into the literature. I wholeheartedly recommend Dr. Chavez, especially to honors freshmen.

Dr. Farmer is a teacher that understands that you don't want to be in his class. But he makes the course material fun and he tries to keep the course load light. Do the readings and take strong notes. His quizzes are based on the readings and they can be tough. However, he's an easier grader than most. I highly recommend that anyone take him.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious

comment: Amazing intro philosophy class. I ended up learning a lot in this class and really enjoyed it. Most of your grade is based off of papers and quizzes. I would highly recommend Dr. Farmer as he is a great guy and lecture was engaging. The class is an easy A if you take good notes in class and follow the rubric on papers.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: He's a great teacher! He gives great explanations and interesting examples. The quizes were hard at first, but you catch on. There are 3 papers and no tests. The papers aren't bad and I didn't think he was too harsh of a grader.

Have 6 reading summary throughout semester which is 30% of your grade. NO EXAMS at all. But he do conduct oral exam about one particular topic of your choice (10%). And 2 critical essay (50%). Easy grader, as long as you understand the material, u'll do just fine.
great teacher really interesting and helpful. Material can be dense and a little dry but he does a good job with it.  But he is a very tough grader, however the class is worth it

Jennings doesn't use a book. You are assigned a team & submit case studies every other week. He doesn't tell you what you're supposed to focus on before you work on the case. You're then graded on whether or not you can guess what he's looking for. Also, it's all manufacturing based. Sorry nonprofit & service sector.

I don't recommend taking his class. He gives out way too much work. He seems like a nice guy and he means well, but his class is very boring and he likes to put students on the spot. He does, however, put a lot of effort into helping you out. Still, don't take him unless you like doing a lot of work.

Participation is a big part of the class.  Doesn't always take attendance but does take note if he calls on a person and they aren't there.  Midterm/Final and weekly homework but that basically goes towards participation.

Possibly one of the worst professors I've ever had.  Makes it a point to make you uncomfortable in class because ''the world is going to make you uncomfortable" so he will pick on you when he knows you dont know the answer.  Nearly impossible to get a good grade on the semester long project. FYI looks like Hitler,

I would take someone else. Nice guy but bad teacher. Grades on participation but doesn't know half the classes name. Participation is worth 8% and you can either get 100%, 60%, or 0%, nothing in between. Teaches right from the book, not interesting, avoid.

This guy is worthless.  He teaches directly from the book.  He takes attendance somewhat so be aware you need to make it to class, even though there's absolutely no reason to.  Multi choice tests, S/A quizes, and a final.
Great TA. I would assume that he would be a great professor as well.

Mr. Zirbel is a very cool cat. He is always excited about teaching and he tells you exactly how your papers are supposed to look. Easy grader, but do not write nonsense. Overall, I recommend for any freshman taking either Rec Comp 1 & 2.
Great teacher! funny and entertaining. very helpful especially if you meet with him. fair grader. speeches were participation grades. would gladly take him again.
Great professor
Hard grader, can be intimating at first. If you want a good grade, at least read spark notes

Fr. Flaherty is a nice guy, but he assigns an insane amount of reading. His 4 tests are ridiculously hard, plus the term paper has no prompt which is not helpful. Lectures are boring and hard to follow.

Rude, treats you like a child. Culturally insensitive. Had him for the second time because he is the only prof that teaches for Dorothy Day and am happy to be done with him. Get on his good side and he'll give you As without merit.

I have fallen asleep in this class too many times to count. He has classes early in the morning which doesn't help with the dense material. He is not clear. He is rude, sometimes culturally insensitive. I would not recommend this teacher to any student.
class is boring but he is helpful in telling you everything you need to know. i had to take a lot of notes. come test time he makes the exam as difficult as possible.
Extremely nice, fair grader, funny guy

This class is based around guest speakers, so she didn't really teach much herself. However, she held office hours to explain things that were on the presentations, and was very clear about what was on the tests. Extra credit was also given, but don't rely on them because they are super specific. The lectures are super interesting!
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: The fact that this class is speaker based is really interesting. Would recommend if you are interested in the crim/law field, or want an easy elective. Exams are easy, just don't bother buying the textbook it's not necessary at all.

This class is speaker based. If you take good notes and attend class, you will get an easy A. Professor Harkins is rarely in class but does pass out attendance in the beginning of lecture. overall, the class is interesting and if you need an elective take this course.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I love the entire CLS department at Marquette. Dr. Harkins's lectures can be slightly confusing at times, but she's such a wonderful professor. She's very understanding and lenient with the learning process. She plays neat movie soundtracks during lab. She's so wonderfully quirky at times. She's also my adviser and she has high respect for me.
she is awesome.  shes very nice and pretty cool to talk to. she tries to make class interesting, but the class itself is really dry, but she helps.  tough grader but fair
Very boring material and class is pretty easy, just make sure you follow her guidelines for the papers exactly.
very easy grader but it is english at marquette so it blows

Brother Lawrence is an easy philosophy teacher. I always just glanced over the reading and managed to get "A's" on every quiz. His lectures are long, but are essentially what will be on the quizzes. A very easy grader and very open minded.
Really boring class, but if you attempt to stay awake/pay attention then you won't do that bad in the class.
He is a decent teacher, but be prepared for his lectures they can be very tedious to stay awake through
Nice guy, pretty easy class, his explanations arent always clear but his tests aren't very challenging anyways. 2 tests, a final, and 5 one page essays throughout the semester.

So unfortunate that this class was required for chemistry majors. Dr. Tran is very knowledgeable, and this class is only moderately difficult. But stay on his good side no matter what. If he does not like you, you are screwed. Go to office hours, talk in class, don't get sick, and prove that you are way smart! It's too easy to get on his bad side.

Pretty difficult course. Take very detailed notes and do all the homework he assigns. If you take bad notes/don't go to class you're not getting an A. If you try hard he will give you the grade you deserve.

He doesn't take attendance but if you aren't there you won't know the answers on some of the test questions. Syas everything is a fair game that you should be prepared for. Very old school and you will never get out early and if you do he will purposely keep you longer the next class period.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Lecture heavy

comment: Dr. Wierzbicki is a great professor. He is very experienced as a clinical psychologist and it's clear that he genuinely enjoys the subject matter he teaches. Class is structured in an understandable way and if you read the book/ go to class somewhat consistently you'll be fine. Also, no long paper anymore (for the personality course).

He's a really nice professor so I feel bad saying that he was not all that great. His lectures would expand upon subject matter that we already understood, when half of the exam questions come from the textbook that he never teaches from. He can also be very monotonous in class

This class had the potential to be SO interesting, but with long tangents and boring lectures, it was not as interesting as I expected it to be. You have to read A LOT or you will not pass his exams. The only good thing I can think of is that he uses a really nice curve when grading exams/papers
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Test heavy--Lecture heavy

comment: The material in Abnormal psychology is fascinating! What's not so fascinating are his teaching skills... I wish I would have taken this class with a different teacher. Smart man but not engaging, makes the class extremely boring and just flat-out mediocre.. I HIGHLY suggest you avoid taking any of his classes. Learn from my mistakes!

He is a nice guy, but the average grade in his class is a C-. An A is a 95%. If you can avoid, then do so. If not you still can survive. Just study really hard. Read both the book and presentation slides.

He is a sweet, old man but does little to engage the classroom in discussion. He has a monotone voice the ENTIRE class period, so it's so easy to lose focus. Most students , including myself, were on our laptops, playing games, or some even WATCHING NETFLIX!!!! I hate to rip on him because he was so sweet!!!

Tests were fairly easy if you study powerpoint material and textbook material. Lectures were pretty boring, but they were manageable. The professor is really nice. The worst part of this class for me was the 12 page paper due at the end of the semester. The final is not cumulative, which is nice.
most boring professor on campus. His lectures are painful and makes even interesting material dry. When I went in for office hours, he was not helpful at all.
Dr. Wierzbicki is a chess master.  Nuff said.

I recommend ot taking thsi class!!! For the theories of personality class most of us failed his tests! Plus there is a 12-15pg paper that counts as 1 test. I had to study as hard for his tests as i had to for chemistry, that says alot DO NOT TAKE.
Was a very good prof.  He challenges his students making his classes demanding but manageable.  The only bad thing is we have a 12-15 page paper and a final :(
Very fair professor.  Tests are straightforward; 50% from class 50% from book (MUST READ THE BOOK).  As long as you read the book and understand concepts from class, you'll be fine.

Favorite class of the semester! Mr. Wierzbicki is a nice guy. He goes through what is going to be on each test the class before. He will help you after class if you stay to ask questions. Tests based on mostly lecture, but the book helps for definitions.

His lectres are boring but not mandatory. They do help but he puts all of his powerpoints on d2l which helps more. You can get throught it without the book but i would still get it. He gives you 4 exams (1 being the final but it's not cumulative) and a 12 pg paper. Very nice guy. And he curves generously.

Pretty nice guy. class is VERY boring for the most part. He is helpful and approachable. The three tests are not easy but he gives a pretty nice curve. Textbook is not huge in the class but you should definitely read it. The worst part of his class is a 12-15 page paper due at the end of the semester. there is also a final

Hes a smart teacher that will help you out whenever you need it. The tests and quizzes are straight from the powerpoints so the textbooks are pointless. Study the slides and it wont be that hard to get an A.
Professor Engel really knows his stuff. I love politics so class went by fast. Lectures are key to success take good notes the power points are online.

Always takes attendance, but lectures are worthwhile, although powerpoints are always on d2l. Tries to interest everyone-not just poli sci majors, and regularly sends out email to help understanding of major concepts. I highly recommend him.

Dr. Engel was great. Extremely helpful & is always ready to answer questions about lectures, readings, debates, news, etc. I took the class as a freshman & I got an A. Did not read everything but still managed to do well by using book as a resource. Overall, a great class & a great teacher especially for freshmen making the transition to college.

He is great! this class was so interesting in regards to knowing your rights and how the supreme court works, I would reccomend this class to anyone. if you go in ad see him, he will help you write an A paper.
I took Dr. Engel for Intro to American Politics and absolutely loved it. He is young, funny and extremely available to answer any questions. A must take for anyone interested in Poli Sci.
He is a great professor and his class may be difficult, but he makes it clear. His office is always open and he makes it easy to learn. Highly recommended.
Don't take him if possible!

Unfortunately, my time with Dr. Berry got cut short due to Covid. However, the few months that I did have with him were great. He is a wonderful professor. The class consists of 4 exams, 1 group project, and 1 paper. Overall, not a very difficult class if you put some effort into it.

The class is lecture heavy and kind of intimidating, but he's a super helpful professor! He gives out the essay question ahead of time and two of the exams had extra credit he also gave beforehand. You can't just go in and wing an exam but if you study and ask him if you have questions, you'll do well!

He gives you the essay question ahead of time. Always extra credit with his tests before hand. One group project. Rest our tests. If you study really really REALLY hard you may do okay. You tend to over study because the tests are almost too simple. MC and T/F are the hardest. Get ready to study!
far out man! Anatomy tends to wreck me but this class wasn't awful, just required hours and hours of studying before tests

Berry is super cool but SO BORING! I found it extremely difficult to pay attention in class. This class was such a struggle but he gives really detailed study guides before tests and extra credit. You're grades are really only based off of the tests and a group project.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--Caring

comment: I LOVED Dr. Berry. He's pretty funny, but the only downside is that his class is in the morning. With anatomy, there's no way you can get by without studying a little. His lectures are not entirely important, but listening can help clarify things later one when you study for his tests. Exams are fairly easy and he's always open to help students.

Dr. Berry makes the class very entertaining and bearable for an early morning class. The material itself is very tough to learn. However, he provides lots of help and is very flexible with time. Overall, a caring man who really cares about his students and their wellbeing.

Dr. Berry is a great teacher. He is always cracking jokes and posts all the lectures online. However, there is a lot of material and a lot of studying is required for a good grade on the exams. Lectures can get long, but his quirky personality helps to get through them. Also, he is very willing to help if you go to his office hours.

The class is tough because of the material, but he makes it fun and engaging! There are a lot of easy points given throughout the semester to balance out a test grade. It is relatively easy, there is no homework or readings, but be sure to study for the tests, they can be tough.
Great professor! Engaging and helpful, most test questions are from his materials  and lectures. make sure to do the extra credit

Dr. Berry is a great professor.  While anatomy can be a challenging course, he takes a lot of time in class really explaining the important topics.  The book is a good aide for this class, but the lectures are the key to doing well.  Show up to class, know the info discussed, and you'll do fine.
FUNNY GUY, KEEPS CLASS INTERESTING. GRADES MORE THEN FAIR AND ALWAYS AVAILABLE FOR HELP. ONE OF MY MORE ENJOYABLE CLASSES, I WISH THEY WERE ALL LIKE THIS!!
Excellent professor. You will know your law after taking his class, but it won't be a breeze.
If you pay attention, get help when you need it, and do your reading, you will do fine. He is incredibly helpful and kind. He makes what should be rather boring incredibly fun!

Professor tells you exactly what he wants in exam answers. If you study, you can do well. He breaks concepts down well and provides ample opportunities to practice and learn the material. He is also an energetic and entertaining professor. Will not embarrass students.
The most enthusiastic instructor I've ever had. Who knew property law could be so fun?

Guilea is a very sweet guy, but he is near incomprehensible in class. But if you ask him, he'll try his best to explain. I say email him, because his writing is extremely scholarly. I say take him, because he's not bad at all.
By far my favorite professor in all of undergrad! She is a unique professor. She is not a typical boring MU phil professor.

The class and tests are easy if you just pay attention. I rarely read and got an A. Yeah she is obsessed with cats and gets annoyed easily but it ends up being really entertaining. She it quite the character.
look her up on facebook its a laugh
Her class isnt hard if you just pay attention. However her attitude is overbearing. She gets annoyed easily, and she is terrible answering questions. Her love for cats is bothersome.

I can't say I enjoyed this class too much. Professor Lapisardi isn't the best at answering questions. But she gives you essay questions before the test, and if you take good notes there is no reason you can't ace her tests.

She knows the material, but does not know how to teach it. It is extremely confusing, and she moves from one topic to another without transitions. She does provide the questions that will be on each exam. However, she is not much help in answering questions prior to the exam.

I took the hist of R&R class and it was the worst class i've ever taken in my life. She quizzed us every week on long articles and podcasts that we would have to read outside of lecture and discussions. Test was a majority of textbook material that she never once mentioned in class. Provided us w a "study guide" that was a list of 75 artists for

Elaine Spiller was THE WORST professor that I've ever had. I took CORE History of Rock and Roll, and I did not learn a single thing. Lectures consisted of in-depth irrelevant content and long youtube clips. Very disorganized and knew nothing about rock and roll. Test was on 2/3 of material never mentioned in class. DO NOT TAKE HER SHE IS THE WORST
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Test heavy--So many papers

comment: Starting this new class has been a train wreck. Core 1929 in particular the Rock and Roll section is just made up as they go. One of the worst experiences in the classroom i have ever had. She just sits and shows power points with 15- 10 minute videos every other slide. And the power points dont discus the book which is 75% of the test questions.

I took linear algebra and matrix theory with her. Dr. Spiller is extremely caring and understanding; however, this is the hardest class Ive ever taken. Lectures are online and homework is supposed to be in class even though we rarely got time to do it in class. I did TERRIBLE on every exam but managed to keep a decent grade with hw and projects.

Dr. Spiller is a terrible teacher for Linear Algebra. It's a flipped classroom, so she doesn't teach. Her video lectures online are unnecessarily long. She makes mistakes frequently. There is no motivation to do anything because the homework is completion, except when you are randomly selected to present homework. Terribly hard class. DO NOT TAKE!!
Confusing, No one in the class knew what was she talking about. Office hours help just confuse the students some more.

No shade but her voice can be a little irritating sometimes (see: when she stretches the words "and" or "so") but overall I would recommend her to pretty much anyone. Most claim Calc II is that hardest of the three Calc courses but if as long as you understand u-sub/integration-by-parts/series convergence tests you'll do well.

Her class is easy, she is extremely friendly, and people don't give her enough credit because they wanted a handout for the class. She lets you redo a test, and gives you extra.. Extremely fair, and the classes weren't hard if you actually paid attention and occasionally did homework. I would recommend taking her again. Awesome teacher

Speak up, she handles questions tactfully.  She uses the board now (no more powerpoint) and her handwriting is better than she thinks it is.  Expect your tests to be graded less generously than the quizzes.  There will be test questions that push your understanding.  Listen in class for problems she's enthusiastic about, they will be on the tests.

If you do not have a calculus background do not dare take her. The class is taught using power points, she does it because her hand writing is not clear, but still, not a good teacher. She does give a lot of free points, but still a pretty challenging class. She wants her students to learn, but she is not a good professor.
Her review methods are stupid; you'll never know if you're doing the problems correctly.

This is by far the worst experience I have ever had in any class. The teacher failed to explain any of the class material in a way that could be understood, instead she merely rushed through the explanations to do examples that are impossible to understand because nothing was adequately explained. Study materials also proved useless in exam prep.
She is really nice but moves way too fast for kids with out a calc background and she tries to force material as much as possible. Any one with out a calc background do not take her!

She is absolutely amazing, her tests are hard but she really helps her students, she's very available and if she's not she will make time. She doesn't like slackers at all and focuses a lot on getting you to actually learn the material instead of just doing it to get it out of the way. The class will make you think of the bigger picture. TAKE IT
LOVE HER

I took Numerical Analysis with her and honestly I thought she was pretty good prof overall. If you show her that you understand the material very well then she will give you a good grade. She doesn't like slackers so work hard! Come during her office hours if you need help! We had a lot of projects, hws and we only had to take one take home exam.

She was a good professor. I liked her a lot. Her class was a lot of work, but I think that's required for stats class. A lot of people in class were slackers, but if you did homework like you were supposed to, you would be fine. She was also very helpful whenever I needed help. Would answer emails quickly. You just have to ask!
She made a lot mistakes in the class and her answers to questions were not clear. She seemed in a hurry to cover a lot of materials but at the end I was not clear why I need all those materials.

Dr. Spiller on multiple occasions seemed if she did not know all the material by making many mistakes.  They could be chalked up to blatant foundation errors where she would side step questions. Her tests were unfair, even the TA questioned the validity of the tests. She had trouble keeping the attention of the class where many studnets fell asleep

I was told that the 2010 fall term was Dr. Spillers first time teaching Calc 1450, having no previous calc experience I found her extremely difficult. Many students with AP calc background had no problem with her class though. She moves very fast. No quizes in quiz section.  No calculators are allowed on test but double sided notecard is allowed.

If you see her teaching Math 4720, please take her!!! She is really a nice person and she really cares about her student's success!! So there are 3 exams plus you can bring a formula sheet. She gives alot of reading quizzes based on the book! And sometimes she give XC to boost your quiz grade! Take her!!

Just reads off the powerpoints, and occasionally elaborates on the board. Don't really have to go to class if you can teach yourself stuff from the book/powerpoints. Tests are not that hard at all. Makes orgo somewhat bearable since the exams aren't too tough. ACS Final exam sucked though.
He's a decent teacher. He does just go through the powerpoint, but he goes through the mechanisms on the board, which helps.

For O-chem, the tests weren't that hard.  They were pretty straight forward and very similar to those in the notes/textbook.  He doesn't do a whole lot of teaching in class, though (just reads a powerpoint). If you can teach yourself well, this is a good class for you.

Dr Sem was one of the worst teachers I have had.  He is very lazy and only clicks through a powerpoint during class.  Don't bother going into office hours because he is equally unhelpful there.  Basically its a class where you need to teach yourself the ENTIRE book out of class.  If this is done well, though, the exams really aren't too bad.

Jennifer is cool and very passive as a professor. Assigns weekly projects that are clear and easy and well explained. Projects are majority of your grade, min quizzes every week or so that are easy if you look at notes. No midterm or final tests, just projects. Mini assignments here and there, a lot of opportunity for points, it'd be hard to fail

Janviere makes a difficult subject (for beginners at least) fun and easy. Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, and InDesign are hard to pick up but she is aware of that and does not grade too difficultly. She is always there to help.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: AWESOME. FAVORITE CLASS THIS SEMESTER. She's so nice and funny and helpful no matter what.

She's awesome. This has been my favorite class at Marquette. Classes were fun and interesting and I always looked forward to class. Ms. Janviere gave clear explanations of all topics covered in class and I really did learn a great deal about the Adobe Creative Cloud software that is central to this class. 8/8 would recommend.
Great teacher! She provides easy instructions and assignments/projects are really easy and can usually be completed with in class work time. She is very helpful and it is really fun. Recommend her!!

I’ve had Dr. Nagurka for 3 classes and all times he has been a challenging but fair professor. I have had great success with his classes, but I also show an interest and willingness to do well. He will not take sleeping and non-attendance lightly, he will notice and not give you the benefit of the doubt. Wish I could have had him for more classes.
Really nice guy and his tests are easy but the homework and labs take a while and are weighed heavily.
Pretty standard. Just contribute occasionally in class and get the work done. He really only actually grades the papers.
Park is the best english teacher. i'd recommend him to anybody looking to take rhetcomp 1 or 2. he's super super nice, always so helpful and is funny in class! he's all around a great teacher

If you're looking for an interesting English class with an intelligent teacher than do NOT take Parkison; he is very offbeat and if you have any thought on a topic that isn't superficial, he probably won't understand it. Blatantly stated: he was a moron.

Park was an awesome teacher, in my opinion. His papers were easy, he was an easy grader, and taught very interesting material. Watched videos in class. As long as you work hard, you'll be fine. A great English Teacher

The worst teacher I've had so far at Marquette.  She is horrible at teaching Pharmacology.  She has very little time to meet with students and will therefore, meet as a big group which isn't very helpful.  The class average for one of our tests was about a 70%-which is 8% below passing.  That goes to show you how poor her teaching skills are.
one of the worst teachers at Marquette. She is very unclear, best chance at getting a good grade is to just teach yourself

Horrible professor!! She doesn't understand the material and cannot teach it. If you don't understand something...google it...don't even bother asking her. She also makes false promises. She will say she will have a grade to you by a certain date...don't listen. It will be weeks later, regardless of whatever empty promises she makes.

The class itself wasn't incredibly difficult.  You had to study hard for the exams, but if you understand case studies they were doable.  This was Dr. Bratt's first time teaching and she was clearly not prepared.  Couldn't answer questions, contradicted herself frequently, mispronounced words.  She was nice, but learning from her was frustrating.

You'll learn more by not coming to class.  She is perhaps the worst instructor I've ever had.  She can't teach, articulate, answer a question.  Her knowledge of the material is highly suspect.  She also has a knack for making inappropriate comments in class.  She is detrimental to the learning process. Brings shame to the college.

I realize that this is her first time teaching Pathophysiology...but she is terrible! She does not understand the material, mispronounces common words (ex: macrophages, alleles), and the students have to correct her often. Since she does not understand biology, she writes very poor exams. Avoid taking her for Pathophy I like the plague!!!

Shes okay, not the best but definitely not bad. Her Powerpoints are unorganized and sometimes hard to follow. She flew through material kind of fast. It seemed like some of the test questions were out of nowhere but she curved them very generously. It's a good class, you learn a lot!

I really liked this class but it's not easy. Her powerpoints have all the information you need to know but the book helps too. She's a fair teacher and is very smart. I would highly recommend this class.

Dr. Bratt is an ok teacher. The material is not very interesting & she doesn't do much to engage the class. She lectures off of ppts & posts them online which is helpful. There are 4 mtpl choice tests (you never really know what's going to be on it, she's always changing things) & you have to make a concept map for a drug - it sucks &takes forever.
Good teacher, fun class, you'll do well if you don't mess around and do your work
good professor class is easy but kind of confused

Very likeable person, not a good class. Avoid this teacher if you can. During the semester, it's extremely hard and tests are irrelevant to lecture material. The final was made up of 90% of previous test questions that you get the answers to however, so that saved my grade.

There is a lot of reading and she doesn't clarify things that well in class. I got more out of the discussion with the TA than I did in lecture with her. The exams were also very difficult. She gave us practice exams to study with and I had graduate biology students help me with them- and even they still got the answers incorrect.

Dlugi isn't a bad teacher by any means. You WILL need to study, and you will need to know what she goes over in class. Yes, she does use powerpoints a lot but she explains things very clearly and actually TEACHES you the subject. Can be inconsistent with what will be on the exam, and she gives pop quizzes, but its manageable and fair enough.

Classes are death by PowerPoint with no thinking required and she teaches as though she's in front of a group of middle-schoolers. This class is nothing but memorizing a large amount of information and then finding out that what you memorized, all the information she presented in class, is useless on the test. Worst class at Marquette.

During the semester, I hated the class. She was not a very good teacher and her tests were hard. However, the final was almost 100% of questions from previous tests and I ended up doing well. The book is very important and definitely get a tutor.
Good Professor! Like every class you have to work hard and do your part to be successful!

Not a bad professor.  Willing to help if you do the work and seek her out.  Obviously hasn't been teaching that long in that clarity could be improved and doesn't manage her class time very well.  Lecture is always behind schedule.  Test questions worded badly. Be prepared to study. A lot. If you don't plan to then drop immediately.

The most frustrating thing about this class was that the way the material was presented in class was not how it was presented on the test. Also what she focuses on in class is not what was focused on on the exams. I would not recommend taking her.

Do not take Dlugi if you can avoid it.  She is by far the worst professor I've ever had.  She does not explain material well at all; she uses only power points with too many words or only pictures that have no descriptions.  Also, her tests are near impossible with averages in the 60's.  Not to mention she is rude and enjoys yelling at her students

DO NOT TAKE THIS PROFESSOR! I repeat. DO NOT TAKE THIS PROFESSOR. She is SO SO boring. i didnt learn anything really. She said in the beginning of the semester that the course would be fun and interesting but it was so the opposite. she likes to use powerpoints with ALOT of words on them. she speaks really fast and doesnt slow down. dont take her!

horrible just horrible...impossible to get high exam scores because all of the questions are analysis and retarded and confusing. she gives study guides that are the opposite of the exam. she's rude and i would never take a class with her again period. plus she enjoys failing everyone

she just flat out sucks, it was more like trivial pursuit:biology edition that it was taking a class where you would expect to learn anything, she basically taught me how to draw a cell and a chromosome. She is really stupid and loves to entertain retarded questions wasting everyones maufudging time. she sucks she sucks she sucks

by far the worst teacher marquettes biology department has to offer. Dlugi seriously made bang my head into the wall after i got every test back because even though i answered every question fully and correctly she would still take points off for not including things she felt were important. however these important things werent asked. shes dumb
Kind of catty (to put it kindly). Goes way too fast and is picky about stupid stuff. Tough grader and has dumb exercises to start class. Avoid
Fine for self-directed learners. A very kind woman, but very light on content, and low expectations of students. Little value added in classroom lecture and discussion.

She is AMAZING. Topics covered in class are current and related to the Bible. She is adorable and so down-to-earth; you have a name and a voice in her class! Online assignments, lots of readings, but totally doable bc you share ur own opinion w/o getting judged. Don't need to be Christian/religious to take this, the class accepts everyone! TAKE HER

I took Dr. Mountin's second year  honors seminar on Jesuit discernment. Classes were often dull and the readings were uninteresting. I did not gain a lot from this class. This was an ok seminar, but I wish I chose a different one.

Susan Mountin is the nicest lady in the planet. She does kind of want to be your mom, though, not your teacher. I haven't learned anything from the class and it is basically a throw away class but if you're looking for an easy class with a nice professor pick her. She will do everything to make it easy on you. Very understanding.

Chad is a wonderful teacher who is very passionate about the subject. He is very willing to help his students succeed. There are only 3 exams that come from class notes, if you attend the class you will do well. The classes are also very discussion based which makes the class go fast. I would take him again.

I love taking his classes! Do the readings, attend office hours (which he has a ton of) and you will do well in his classes!  He is great, and cares about his students! My favorite professor so far!! :)
The best professor I've ever had.  He's funny and very helpful with every topic he talks about.  He has a lot of office hours and you can get a hold of him all the time
He is a real gem. Always kind, and really cares about what he teachers. Students might not always be the most attentive, but he knows a lot of stuff.

The best way to describe Dr. Corliss is he is very technical. He has been teaching for a long time so he knows his stuff, but he is a little hard to connect with. Overall his lectures are pretty beneficial.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Difficult class.

He's an average prof.  Easily side tracked in lecture and not very easy to follow.  He's extremely AR about his testing procedures, but the past decade of exams are online, so basically memorize them and you'll be fine.  He's already a professor emeritus, not sure why the University has him stick around, he should just go into retirement already...

I've had Dr. Corliss as an advisor, a professor, and as a supervisor. He is extraordinarily sharp and his explanations cut confusion. He is not an easy professor by any means, but that should not discourage you from taking one of his courses. Expect to learn something every time you hear Dr. Corliss speak. He also uses funny and relevant stories.
Gave WAY to much HW.

If you are thinking about taking this class as an elective do not do it. I have never heard of any class assigning this much work. If you want to complete all of the assignments you won't have a life. You're basically writing a book about music every week with absurd guidelines. This class is hell. Seriously, you have been warned DO NOT TAKE.

Took this class over summer online.  Wow was it easy but since it was online it was "discussion based" and WOW was there A LOT to write.  Discussions, discussion responses, 2 "listening logs" that involved analyzing 10ish pieces, and activities. Every week was probably 8-12 pages of VERY EASY writing, just time consuming. EXTREMELY EASY

Prof. Ladd is perhaps the worst Orchestra conductor I have ever had. Join symphony just because it's fun and the musicians are just amazing, but the director is completely incompetent and he is the most conceited person I have ever met. Definitely avoid if possible.

He's very entertaining but as a teacher he isn't that great. He gives a lot of homework, weekly pop quizes which he doesn't really explain ahead of time and a midterm/final. He tries really hard but is bad at explaining the material. Overall not that great but the only MUSI2500 teacher so....

Orchestra Director - Dr. Ladd is very funny and interesting but is more familiar with Band music than Orchestra.  Highly recommend doing Symphony but he needs to work on String Pedagogy more. Since he's a tuba player, Dr. Ladd is more knowledgeable with brass as apposed to strings; even though a symphony is primarilly strings. overall, good teacher

Ladd knows pretty much everything there is to know about theory,but he is prob one of the worst profs I've had at Marquette. I think he believes that his class is the only class, even though he gives you a week to turn in HW the HW takes about an hour or more a night.I had to re-teach everything on my own. This prof should not be allowed to teach

I took this class with him over the summer! There was about 5 exams that was worth 80% of my overall grade.  Just come to class, takes notes off the powerpoints and familiarize yourself with the terms from the book. If you do all of this, then this class shouldn't be problem for you! Its easy an A!

I had Dr. Ladd for music theory. It is a very easy class if you have had some theory background before. He is always willing to help. He gives quizzes, and if he notices that people didn't understand the material, he comes up with new ways to explain it. He assigns homework every day, which might seem like a pain, but it actually helps your grade.

Hands down the worst professor in the Engineering Management (ENMA) program. Has no idea what he is doing and class has no value. While he should be teaching us about project management, he goes on and on about his past experience and stories. I feel the students learned more from each other than from him. If it was up to me he would never get PhD
She is extremely nice and allows you to redo every paper. It is almost impossible to get lower than an A in her class.

I would not take her if you get offended easily. Very liberal and often goes off on tangents about various social issues. If you do the readings you should do pretty well. Attendance is not mandatory but she awards a half letter grade bump at the end of the semester for perfect attendance

Dr. D's english class is pretty easy.  Make sure you read the instructions for her papers and you should be fine.  Take advantage of her "2 paper" revision policy! She's pretty lenient when it comes to paper revisions.  However, she gives too much busy work for homework.  Overall, decent class if do well on papers and follow directions.

Dr D is the BEST english teacher i have ever taken.  She is so chill, and just loved to give life lessons quite often during class.  The essays are a breeze, and she is clear with what to expect.  Dr. D has so much depth, stories, and sass.  SUCH an awesome lady.  You will miss out if you attend MU and don't get to know Dr. D.

Fantastic teacher. Easy A. You really don't do anything in class except listen to her rant. Just use fancy vocabulary in your paper and make a clear point and you'll get an A. Like everyone else said, if you only miss 1 class during the semester you get raised a grade. Highly recommend her.

This class is a joke.  show up to every class and it is impossible not to get an AB.   She goes off on rants and is not a good teacher, but then again it is english....   the only reason to go to class is turn things in.  Take this her for an easy A, but try to find a better teacher who is enjoyable

Easy A. Go to class and get your grade raised half a letter. She can be frustrating, she gives stupid busy work assignments but theyre really easy and take no time. You get to rewrite your papers until you get an A on them. Definitely a class worth taking for an easy A.

Super easy. Homework literally takes 15 minutes. She is really laid back, she wants you to get an A. It is almost impossible to get below a B. If you go to every class she raises your grade by a half a letter grade.

I love this professor. She is really effective in communicating lecture material as well as what you should expect on the tests. She is really easy to talk to and genuinely cares about your success both as a student and in your professional careers.

Dr. Berg is the best professor at Marquette, hands down. She is very relatable and understands that we are students and have a million things going on. I've done to her office multiple times for advice (PR is my major), and she is SO helpful!! Loved PURE1800. Interesting, learned a lot, and overall fun with Dr. Berg! Take her - even as an elective!
had her for campaigns and it was fun! shes very accessible if you need help with your campaign book or presentation. the whole class was graded on participation, 2 tests, and the book.

I love Dr. Berg! I took this class kind of for fun (I'm not a PR major) and it was amazing! The discussions were really interesting and the assignments got you thinking- no busy work. All I can really say is I love her! If you have the chance to take her-- do it AND get to know her! She's an awesome lady that will be there for you in the future!

Well groomed on the class material, is very clear about what she's talking about. She makes it achievable to get good grades on tests and presentations with good prep. She is so sweet. interesting and gives lots of opportunities for points for participation and assignments. Sometimes, is hard to get in contact with but does her best.

Dr. Berg is wonderful and her class is a lot of fun! There are readings for each class, but they are usually short. This class was largely based on opinion, so she was a pretty easy grader. No tests, just some small assignments and a few projects (2 group projects). I would definitely take a class with her again!

Dr. Berg is the most helpful and down to earth professor in the College of Communication at Marquette. She is also always willing to meet for office hours even though she lives an hour away. Take time to do your work ahead of time and she will help give quality feedback so you not only get a good grade but retain the information. Great class!

Dr. Berg is so nice and helpful. At least one quiz every two weeks, one paper, and a couple tests. If you listen and class and take notes off the powerpoint it is super easy. Definelty a teacher I would take again. If you are interested in public relations take her
Great teacher, cares for students. Try to be on her side and not get in an argument it will go a lot smoother.
Very good professor but the tests are difficult.

Dr. Berg is awesome, she makes the class entertaining and interactive. She is modern and makes a lot of recent examples. Test aren't as bad, but you should still study. Class isn't hard to follow. She expects students to participate, therefor she is a hard participation grader.

Dr. Berg is an excellent instructor. Her ADPR 1800 class was interesting and engaging. She was a fair grader on the 3 multiple choice and short essay tests as well as the one paper. I highly recommend this class.
great teacher!! so nice and very easy loves to help her students with as much as she can - take her if possible!!
attendance is mandatory. will be dropped.
Amazing teacher! Energetic and fun! Very pretty. Into running. Know how to make a boring-ish subject fun! Take her if you can!
TJ Meehan is difficult and should be, he is training medical professionals.

People complain this class is hard, but anatomy NEEDS to be hard. He tells you to study every day and honestly if you dont you will suffer the consequences. It is definately a difficult course but it IS a five credit hour course. If you study as he tells you to and actually pay attention in lecture, you may not get an A but you'll pass.
has a very odd sense of humor. answers questions in long drawn out responses.  Tests are very specific.  Dont touch models with pencils

Great professor. Notes are nothing but power points that if you memorize, you'll be fine. He is willing to help you as much as you need and give you whatever needs possible to succeed. Take him, you will not regret it.

Difficult to follow. Expects you to come to class already knowing the material. Expects you to know a TON of material/details for the tests. Lots of reading. The class is ok, just frustrating and time consuming. He also calls people out for not paying attention, so don't mess around on your laptop.
Content of class is sometimes difficult, but she is there whenever you need help and she's an awesome teacher. very interesting and mind-stimulating lectures. she really cares about her students
She's the best. 3 grades: a paper, midterm, and final paper. Very helpful on all. Class is all discussion, someitmes boring but usually stimulating.

She is an amazing teacher. Doesn't make you feel like you don't know anything rather helps you determine what you know. Harder than usual grader for papers but really goes above and beyond to help you and if you talk to her you'll do well. Really nice, too.

Great personality, great professor. The Trusts & Estates exam can be deceivingly hard if you're not adept at taking law school multiple choice exams. Attendance isn't mandatory, but you should be there, if nothing else, for his priceless quotes. Take a class with him!!!

I thought he was a great teacher. Had no interest going in, but he got me to like trusts & estates and made it easy to learn. Funny, approachable, very smart & knowledgeable, easy to listen to. Doesn't take attendance, not sure he even knew anyone's name. Sit in the back if you don't want to get called on. Test was multiple choice and kind of hard.

THE BEST professor I have had at MU. I hate spanish, but he was an excellent teacher. Speaks slowly enough to understand and will explain something in English if you just aren't getting it. Wish I had him again this semester.
one of the best spanish professors i have ever had. If you don't understand something he will explain it to you in english if need be

He is a wonderful teacher. He can speak the language, but at the same time goes slow enough to comprehend him. The tests are tough for me (I'm terrible at Spanish), but the tests are all identical for whichever teacher you take. Class participation is a MUST! All homework is online every night.

He is a good teacher for the grammatical aspects of spanish.  Likes to see student participation.  A lot of group working in class through the text book.  He is very clear about what will be in the exams and always willing to meet outside of class.  Constantly makes sure people are following his lecture.  overall good teacher.

Silver-thorn is a very smart and helpful professor. Probably the only class I cared about last semester with the interesting subjects and field trips to relevant locations. No homework, but this is a ruse as the tests are ridiculous, luckily it is on a graduate scale so a class avg of 60% is good.  Hard class but if you enjoy it, it is worth it.

Dr. ST is a very knowledged teacher. One of the best i have had at MU. She provides you with all the power point lectures and helps you as much as possible to pass the class. However, you have to work for the grade. The class material itself is difficult. She does a great job teaching it. Her tests are all application based, no memorization.

Quite Confusing.She is known as a good teacher in all her other classes but in this one she really has dropped the ball. lab and lecture are totally different. if you wanna learn how to code, she is not the teacher to take for this class. she doesnt teach any code, ya gotta learn it yourself for lab.
She is a great person. She is very helpful when it comes to meeting her at her office hours. She is the reason I am at Marquette

His homework is absurd. It is impossible to tell what he is asking for and impossible to understand what he is doing in his "sample problems". His lectures are almost pointless as he breezes over almost everything and gives very little insight into homework problems. The man quotes himself on his into presentation on the first day of class

This will be your most frustrating class. You will ask what is going on the entire time, I am about to take the final and still have no clue what somethings are despite getting the answer right. You won't get an A but you won't fail.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: Very nice guy, but crappy teacher. He writes his own book which is very confusing - good luck trying to understand/follow it. Lectures are walls of text and not clear at all. Also each HW problem could be a HW assignment in itself, and you can get higher scores on D2L quizzes just by guessing and not actually doing them. Take Beardsley if you can.
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Winters is very smart, but not good at teaching. You will not understand the topics and it will not help to study old tests. You won't fail, but you won't get an A either. Luckily he's getting more group project based and he is a much better alternative than scheidt is. Just put your head down and push through and it will be ok.

Dr. Winters is a difficult professor - he's not always clear in his expectations, but he genuinely cares about all of his students and hopes that they do well. He's just not willing to compromise material difficulty for higher test scores. I've come to really enjoy his teaching style and his massive amount of knowledge. He's an all around good guy.

Singular worst professor that I have ever had. He is extremely smart, but totally ineffective in conveying that information to students.  His classes require more work than any other 3 classes that you will ever take combined. Tests are confusing and are more about regurgitation of random data than demonstrating understanding.  Avoid at all costs!
He is confusing but if you are willing to put forth about 6 credits worth of effort you will get an A
Loved her class! She was so nice, question of the day might have been the best part about it. And kind of pleasing to the eye.
The papers make up your whole grade, she tries to make a boring class at least worth taking.
I'd take her again, obviously tries to make a dull class tolerable
Sweet and understanding for the most part. FOur papers make up your whole grade, but she's pretty clear about instructions.

Very nice and helpful. I felt that she graded pretty gently, but even my AB papers had lots of advice and suggestions on them. Definitely knows what she is doing. I think she is pretty unbiased when grading papers. I liked her!

She definitely has her own style of writing and unless you conform to that style, it is hard to earn a good grade on her essays. The class is not overly difficult but I found the essay portion to be the biggest part of my grade and with her strict style of writing, it made it hard to really go outside the box.
Is always availabe for outside help, but use it because sometimes papers can be hard to write without it. Funny, tries to keep class fun.
Ugh. This woman made my life a living hell. She is totally unreasonable and is extremely nitpicky...its almost as if she LIKES taking points off of your grade. AVOID AT ALL COSTS!!!!

Easiest college class ever. I didn't buy any of the books. If you have her old tests, you're getting an A. She barely changes them and the points that you do get deducted from the test, you could make up in easy extra credit. Take turns going to class with friends so you can sign each other in the 3 times she passes around a sign in sheet.

Mrs. WInkler was a very easy teacher. If you have prior tests you will do fine since she barely mixes up her questions. Also includes 10 points extra credit so she knows which kids want more points. Takes attendance 3 times in the semester that will count as 15 points each, and she is a pleasing to the eye.

This class was not as easy as I thought it would be. I showed up to all of the 8 am classes and did all of the readings and it was not an easy A. It was annoying that people in the class had the old tests and would not show up to class but still get an A. Nevertheless, she is the professor to take if you need an anthro credit!

This is a great class to take for an elective.  She assigns a lot of reading, but there is no need to read the textbook chapters, since she goes over it all in class.  She obviously really likes the subject and knows what she is talking about.  However, she has a little bit of an obsession with sexual activity  and shows videos of apes having sex.

Took her for Intro to Anthro. Just my luck - she decided to revamp the curriculum this semester so it wasn't as easy as I thought it was going to be and tests were different from previous years. Part-time prof, held office hours 7-8am which was annoying. Attendance optional, but those who didn't go did not do well.

Her class was extremely easy. The old tests are very similar and reading the book is basically unnecessary. I didn't study and received an A. She also gives out extra credit that helps a lot! Overall, the class was easy and interesting.

She was a great teacher! Her lectures were very clear and she was helpful outside of class to clarify anything. Exams are very easy. She reuses exams from previous years. While she requires a lot of reading, you don't need to read to get an A on her tests
Super easy teacher, no homework. Doesn't change tests very much so if you find someone with previous years tests, you are preeettyy much guaranteed an A. Highly recommend her as an anthro professor!
Lectures are easy, can get boring. She's a very nice teacher. Tests are pretty simple if you study for them.
awesome teacher! he is clear in his teaching and gives the needed instructions. very helpful. always available for office hours and many times after office hours. TAKE him!

Mr. G is a great english professor.  His instructions are clear and his comments on the papers are actually helpful.   He makes class interesting and worth going to.  All assignments are turned in online and he is a fair grader.  He makes himself available before each paper is due just in case you have questions.Take him if you have the chance.

Mr. G is, by far, the best English professor I have ever had throughout my whole life. I came into this year as a freshman who was not a fan of English, but Mr. G made class fun and interesting. He is extremely funny and helpful, and gives great feedback on all of the papers and short writes you have to do. If you have the chance, take Mr. G!

Mr G is awesome! Not only is he funny, he makes himself very available for any questions you might have.
