He makes appointment times before every paper is due, and gives great feedback while grading the papers. I work hard on my papers, but other than that, the class is manageable and all around a great experience (and I don't even like english) !

Dr. G. is great. He has one of those subtly hilarious senses of humor. Unlike some professors, he really cares. If you put in effort, you'll do well for sure. If you don't have all your books, it's not a big deal, cause he posts the readings on D2L. (By the way, I recommend not buying the freshman ENGL package by yourself. Split it with a friend.)

He was an amazing teacher. He was always willing to help whenever you needed him and always stressed his office hours. He worked hard to get to know his students and have them be comfortable with him. I would recommend him to ANYONE!
He is really the sweetest and will go out of his way to help bring clarity to the material. He can get off track, but he is always in a great mood and very passionate about HR.

I had him for Remedies.  He was absolutely terrible.  He blatantly admitted he doesn't prepare for classes.  His grading system is ridiculous--you take group tests and one incomprehensible final--and he is an arbitrary grader.  Take the class if you want to waste your tuition money and lower your GPA.
Google his name. Easy class, though.

Grad student, had him for macro, very easy.  Allows use of note sheet for tests, teaches directly off power points which he posts on d2l.  He also assigns problems for homework and take home quizzes that are identical to questions on exams.  Tries to be engaging but not successful.

He is a grad student and seems pretty nervous when teaching. He literally teaches from the book so its easy if you just keep up with the reading on the syllabus. He also gives practice tests which are nearly identical to the actual test.

Dr. Bergen is not an Easy A, but instead  teaches you how to write. He takes the full class time every time and really cares about his students. Papers are straight forward on what he wants. Dr. Bergen wants to teach you how to write and it will help you immensely later in your college career. He is extremely nice, take this class.

TAKE THIS CLASS! Absolutely LOVED this class because Dr. Bergen was AMAZING! You have to put in time and effort but not even that much. It is obvious that Dr. Bergen loves what he does and has best interest for his students. He DOES NOT want any of his students to fail and is the best English teacher that I have ever had. Seriously take this class!

I didn't do a single reading the entire semester...didn't take notes either, but Dr. Bergen is a pretty funny guy and its not hard to listen to him...pretty easy grade...even though i didn't read or study i got a C on both exams and A's on everything else. And i actually think i learned about it as well. Take his class, you will not regret it.

I had little interest in British Lit but out of the classes that were open, Dr. Bergen had the best reviews and I do not regret taking the course at all. Class is interesting and while there is reading for every class (duh it's lit) you can pay attention in class and be fine. 5 D2L posts, 2 5-6 pg papers, 2 1 pg pps, midterm and final.

AMAZING PROFESSOR!Really cares about the students, if you need help he will MAKE SURES you understand it. TAKE THIS PROFESSOR! Lots of readings but I never read and did just fine, four total papers and one revision. EXCELLENT TEACHER! YOU WONT REGRET TAKING THIS CLASS, you need work to get an A, but he has NO interest in failing you.

Take this class!! it is super simple the way he teaches and he does things to keep you interested. I never do reading and its fine, he goes over them in class. Papers are the same in most class and he is really good and telling you what to write and how to do, he likes to help. but you do have to go to class!
Love this class!!!! Granted there is a lot of reading from the textbooks but bergen is super nice and very very sweet and really understanding. :)

I took this class and I LOVED it! Although I have seen the majority of the material prior to taking this class, it was interesting. There are 3 test and 2 papers which are super easy. Class notes are vital. Overall, good history teacher and good class for getting a solid A
She gets angry at students for asking what time it is.

Very accomodating. She is very stict about detail but she explains what she wants. She is always willing to help you if you have a problem and she drops your two lowest quiz grades. She assigns extra credit. 2 papers 1 assignment. She gives you the study guide 2 weeks in advance. Take the class easy A or AB if you try!

Lecture is fairly pointless but she follows attendance pretty strictly. The book is your best friend for exams and hope you have a fair TA as he grades everything. If you insist on taking good notes, writing them is useless. She talks so fast, a laptop is necessary (and allowed). Dont procrastinate studying for exams and know dates of events.

She is hard to listen to. She gives you a study guide for the tests which is helpful. She does not grade anything, the TA grades everything. I would go to your TA for help since he/she grades everything. If you study for the tests and go to class you will be fine.

First of all, her voice is horrible and takes forever to get used to. You sign in everyday for attendance, however you can ace the test without going to a single class. Tests are rediculous and require a whole weekend of studying. 2 tests, 2 papers (one long, one short), 1 final, and participation points. Boring, but not impossible.

Take her if you want to fall asleep in class. BORING lecture that seems pointless when it comes to the test. Go to class or i would advise making a friend and switch off signing each other in. Her voice is annoying. Her tests are okay - but just use the book and forget about lectures. Dont bother with reading the books for discussion. sparknote it

Attendance is taken, and I suggest going to class...missing a lecture means missing a LOT of stuff, and the outlines posted online are just a list of words that were covered in lecture, so they're no help.
Nice lady. Tests are easy but if you have a strict TA you will loose points on essay.  Fair teacher. I would take her again.

Pretty average teacher.  Sort of dull lectures every day, but she usually lets you go a few minutes early. For tests she gives a study guide with all the terms for the short answer & essay questions, and will usually take several off before the test.  Not necessary to use the book, but I found it helpful for looking up terms.  Pretty boring though.

Dr. Witkowski is a fair teacher, her goal isn't to screw you over and she does cut the terms and essays to study for the test in half. Don't buy the book unless you want to waste money, however buy the ones needed for discussion. Discussion is every couple of weeks and on the days there is discussion, there is no lecture. Also, sit up front!

Take her! You don't need to read the book, just go to lecture and take notes.  She is really nice and means so well. Her study guides for the tests tell you EXACTLY what you need to study for, and a week before the test she will cut 1/2 the terms and 1 of the essays, making it that much easier to study for. She will answer your questions online too
Easy, but impossible to listen to.  She means well but isn't the best teacher out there. I'd try to find someone else...

Do not take this professor. She is impossible to listen to, very hard to follow. Powerpoints are useless, lectures are a waste of time. You need to use your textbook to learn anything at all. Change your professor right now.

Awesome teacher always trying to crack some jokes and make the class as fun and enjoyable as possible. In addition he is a fair grader and thrives to try his students to improve. Definitely recommend taking this professor.

One of my favorite teachers.  Very fair grader- you have to actually try, and personable. He takes his class seriously but isn't afraid to joke around. I think he really tries to get to know his students. Oh, and he's pretty hot.
I had a very hard time understanding what each paper was supposed to consist of.  he provided very little guidance and is a hard grader.
He makes you work for an A. His directions were always clear, but this isn't a high school english class. He's funny to listen to and sometimes shows random youtube videos.

Lorino was a cool guy. He's young (and gorgeous) but pretty serious about the job. The first two papers were difficult but not hard to get a B if you're a good writer. The second two were a breeze. Your final is take home--a revision of one of your previous papers. He isn't always the most helpful/clear with instructions but the class was ok.
Cool teacher. He grades somewhat tough but he gives you everything you need to know in order to do well

great teacher, makes things really clear in his handouts and tells you exactly what his expectations are. Advice: Do not miss class because he may change rubric and won't tell those absent. He knows this is a core class and does his best to make the material more interesting.

pretty easy grader, got an AB in his class. he's always willing to meet with you and always asks if people have questions to clear things up. i did well on his papers, just a boring class as most english courses are

I took this class because I heard good things about Professor Huggard. However, this was my lowest grade of the semester, even though I put in a lot of effort and did all of the readings. He expects too much out of you for an intro class.  I would steer clear from him as a professor if possible.

Professor Huggard is a very nice and approachable man. He is more than willing to give assistance or help you after class. Some things I did not care for however were that 60% of your grade comes in the last two weeks of class. Also, many of the materials and grades on d2l were unorganized and distributed untimely. Challenging for a intro class.

My FAVORITE professor at Marquette yet. He really cares about his students and wants to see them thrive and succeed in his course. He is so smart and funny so his lectures are very interesting. He does give pop quizzes so make sure you attend class every day and READ. I would recommend him to everyone. He doesn't try and make you believe in God.
AMAZING teacher! My favorite professor here by far.

I ABSOLUTELY LOVED PROFESSOR HUGGARD. He literally knew all of our names by the 2nd week of class, and really cared about everyone as an individual.  He has so much knowledge to share, and really taught me a lot.  Plus he's not so bad to look at either. I recommend him!!

AWESOME - Huggard is my all time favorite prof I've ever had as was his class. He's incredibly intelligent and really passionate about the material. Comical, well cultured, always willing to stay after and talk about anything. Work is easily doable, just do the reading and/or pay attention in class. Super easy "pop" quizzes, one paper, 2 exams.

If you can, TAKE HIM!!!! He realizes everyone comes from different religious backgrounds and is respectful of other people's opinions. Will give a study guide before each exam. As long as you know everything on it, you'll get an A. Easy class, but do study.

Prof. Huggard is a very good teacher.  He is very clear and is passionate about the subject he is taking.  He really impressed the students when he invited those who weren't going home for Easter to Easter dinner with his family.  The best theology teacher at Marquette.
Huggard is a great teacher. HE is an easy teacher for theo. He is interested in what he does and it was an easy AB for someone who never took religion classes
Great teacher! Loves what he teaches and is enthusiastic about it. Brings in personal stories to teach but you almost need previous catholic knowledge or be very detail aware as you read.

He was very interesting and related to the students. He's definitely the best theo teacher and doesn't assign absurd amounts of work. His quizzes and tests are almost identical to his study guides and lectures

Huggard is by far one of my favorite teachers at Marquette! He is young energetic and understands what its like to be a student. He always has the most refreshing stories about his family. His class lectures are interesting even though the content is relatively boring in and of itself. His quizzes and grading style is pretty easy.

Alex is a super amazing theology teacher. He made class very interesting and the material was easy to understand. He hinted at when we would have "pop" quizzes and he was very good about answering any questions anyone had. Just read and you will do fine. He tried to use real life comparisons. We watched clips of scrubs at least 3x.
He really cares but is kind of a hard grader.  Willing to help his students if you go seek him out.

Kelley is an excellent teacher.  He is obviously very new and young, but that gives the class energy and can relate to his teaching.  The class became very close by the end of the semester, and was comfortable chatting with Kelley.  The coursework consists of short writes and 4 papers: something that is certainly doable. Take this class!!!
Awesome professor, much better than that of ENGL 1001. He gives us 5 papers and asked us for the fifth paper to repeat and substitute any of the first four papers.

I loved his class. I had HATED my previous ENGL1001 class so this was a huge relief for me.  He's a young, funny, very down to earth and aware of his students type of guy.  He doesn't lecture, he lets everyone in the class openly discuss topics and it makes it fun and interesting. He grades papers fairly and gives tons of feedback. I'd recommend!

He's an incredibly nice, funny guy, but he's the youngest teacher I've had, and my first impression was that this might be his first time teaching. Seems aware of where he needs improvement (clarity!), and gives help if you ask, but with the way he explains concepts, sometimes I feel I'd do better in this class if I didn't attend the lectures.

Dr. Kaugars is such a sweetheart! She is a great professor and genuinely cares about her students. Attendance and reading the book are key to passing her class, but she is always willing to help you if you need it. She is such a happy person and will make class enjoyable, so I would really recommend her!

The class is very fast paced, but she is very entertaining and engaging during class. She responds to emails somewhat quickly when there are question, but it takes her a long time to grade things (possibly due to her involvement in research). It's a heavy workload, but keeping up with studying and reading isn't too impossible.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Amazing lectures

comment: Her lectures are super boring, she usually just stands up there and read from a piece of paper, lotssss of busy work, service learning is a pain plus to 5 papers you write for it. the tests are hard because they are half short answer and you need to put exactly what she wants to get points, do the objectives before the test and you should be ok

It was an interesting class but the tests are half multiple choice and half free response. The tests can be tricky but she always put up the objectives from each class which are helpful to study from. I would recommend this class.
Great teacher but need to do a lot of outside reading and work to get a good grade in the course.
His only flaw is his handwriting. Cannot read a thing, but he knows what he is talking about and a great professor.

He was by far the worst professor I have had. If you have taken calc 3 you have a better chance of passing. He expects you to already know the material before hand and is terrible at explaining the material. Would not recommend.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Lectures are OK, takes a bit to get used to the heavy accent.  When he gets on his rants or offshoots, he gets more excited, causing him to talk faster, and it gets to the point that you can no longer understand him.  He does have an open door policy, and invites questions, however he seems very biased.  Good looking uber-liberal girl?  Your good.
At first I liked Dr. Jones, but then I realized he didn't really teach that well. He was difficult to understand and was often times very rude to students. I would not recommend.

Any Calc experience and you'll ace the class. All homework is online, and if you get above an 80% on the homework it curves up to 100. I did not purchase the text book. Attendance was taken two or three times in lecture, that being said his tests will be much easier if you actually show up daily. He is a bit hard to understand sometimes though.

If you have not taken Calculus before, avoid this class like the plague. His explanations are abysmal and his handwriting is worse, so taking notes in his class is essentially futile. The TA that I was stuck with has an incredibly strong Nepalese  accent, with terrible handwriting as well. Will likely have to retake class with a different professor

Would not take again. Doesn't know how to explain simple concepts, yet asks us to "apply" those concepts on the test. The only reason I am passing this class is because of outside sources (i.e. Khan Academy, YouTube, etc). He does not teach well/at all.  I would not suggest him to anyone.

His lecture notes are not written well and are often very hard to read which makes the material harder to understand. He is a nice guy but he over complicates simple concepts in exams and is not clear in what he asks for.

Awesome professor! Complete with an Australian accent, he keeps class fun and entertaining. He sometimes rambles into proofs during lecture, but his discussion sections and quizzes clear up anything you may miss in class. He is always available to help students and knows his entire class by name. Go to class! He drops heavy exam hints!

Dr. Jones is a wonderful Calc prof. He cares about making sure we understand the theory behind each problem. He explains how each problem can be visualized and applied. Besides those explanations, he uses class time to do example problems. It's perfect really. I would take his classes again and again if I could.

Dr. Jones knows what he is talking about. However, he goes off in different directions and over explains simple material.  He is a nice and helpful guy, but you have to go to him for help, he won't go out of his way to help you, which is understandable. I've had him for 2 different classes and would not recommend him.

Dr. Jones is a very knowledgeable and caring professor.  He genuinely cares about the success of his students.  His class is very straightforward and fair.  His tests are moderately challenging, but every question is something you've seen before either in the quiz section or in the homework.  I'd definitely recommend him.

Dr. Jones seems knowledgeable about the subject but he skips around and spends up to fifteen minutes on tangents that almost no one can follow. He knows what he's talking about, if you can pay attention.   If you can take him, take him. I had a great TA that helped me a lot, but I could have gotten through with just Dr. Jones. He's a cool guy.

This class is very straightforward and with the quiz sections each week, it helped keep me on track for the tests. Surprisingly I think that calc 3 was the easiest of the calcs! Except for the last section of the semester with flux kinda had me lost. He is a very nice and personable professor who knows and enjoys what he's talking about, take him!

Great professor. He has an Australian accent that takes about a day to get used to, but he is very clear during lectures. If you take notes and are willing to actually work through them on your own to understand them then you shouldn't have too much of a problem. His tests are fairly difficult, but they are fair. Just study in class problems.
Good teacher, I never tried to visit his office hours because his TA (Ben) was so good and always available. Went out of my way to schedule him for calc 3 next semester because I liked him so much.

Show up ON TIME or prepare for "the look." Australian accent, but incredibly understandable! The tests aren't a surprise, but they get harder as you go, he expects you to keep up with homework, and you need to in order to understand. Quiz sections, the TA's do tons of example questions! Super handy! Gives study guide for each test!Takes attendence!

Super good proffessor. Tests are not meant to trick you. They are very straight forward. The final test is hard, but all the other exams and quizzes are fair. He does lots of example problems in class.

Dr. Jones is a very smart guy who has trouble communicating his ideas to others. Calculus II is not an incredibly difficult subject, but the way he explains simple ideas makes them confusing. His tests are not huge surprises, but there is no practice other than the homework questions that you can redo.
Very good teacher. Extremely recommended

He is very helpful during office hours and he does want students to understand the topics and get a good grade in the class. The test is not totally hard, but it covers all materials covered in the class. So, if you miss any classes, make sure you know what he covers in the class.
Australian Accent. Teaches well. Pretty relaxed about grades and is generally a nice guy and helps if you encounter some problems.

This guys knows his stuff. The first 2 weeks may be a bit rough, but once you get past his thick and heavy austrailian accent, things will go smoother. The only thing you need to worry about in Calc2 are Series and Work Problems, both of which Jones explains very well (although Series is very hard). Overall good teacher, I would recommend him
Decent teacher. Goes on tangents and over explains, makes it hard to grasp the main concept. If he likes you he's easy to talk to. USE OFFICE HOURS! Has an Austrilan accent, fun guy.

Really really great teacher.  He is extremely helpful and clear.  He is very organized and tells you exactly what you need to know on the tests.  As long as you actually do the work, you'll get an A.  Take him!
Dr. Lashier is very nice, he's not as up tight as you would expect a theology professor to be. Doing the readings will help you on the pop quizzes, but for they tests, they don't matter.

AMAZING PROFESSOR! He knows what he's talking about and is very thorough with the material. Keep up with reading, as it is very important. However, the reading was not long and pretty enjoyable. Fantastic class...I definitely recommend his class to everyone!

Awesome professor, definitely recommend him. Only 3 tests and 2 papers. Reading quizzes can be tough, so keep up with the material but he's very helpful and makes class enjoyable. Take his class! You'll love it!
Very nice, easy if you listen in class but a hard grader for papers!
He was one of my favorite professors and I dreaded taking theology.  He made class interesting and was very chill.  One of the best teachers at Marquette hands down!
This Guy Is Super Chill.  Great Class, And He Really Know His Stuff.  One Big Paper, 3 Tests, 2 Mini Papers, And 8 Pop Quizes. Great Class

Lashier just knows what's up. His class is very interesting, and he really knows his stuff. He's always willing to offer help outside of class, and he's just a good guy to talk to in general. I DEFINITELY recommend his class. Two thumbs way up.

Lashier is a total sweetheart, and one of my favorite professors so far. His class is easy enough but also interesting, and you actually learn something. He's always willing to help, and really cares about his students a lot. He's a wonderful person and a wonderful teacher. Plus hes a cutie!

Absolutely fantastic teacher. Managed to make an intro theology class at 8 AM interesting. Very friendly, helpful, and approachable. If I have the opportunity to take a class of his again I definitely will.

She is a very nice teacher and is extremely interested in the subject that she teaches.  She is willing to help students and provides a lot of office hours and extra practice websites for students.  Arsc is a difficult class and she does have high expectations for what her students should be able to do.

Karrie is a nice lady but not a good teacher at all. She barely teaches any of the material in class and the rest of the material on the exams arent even in the book. Her TA's do a lot of the work. The quest questions are taking directly from online tests. She explains problems wrong. This is a very frustrating class. Avoid this class with her.

Karrie is a downright horrendous proffessor. Any question takes half an hour of class time to answer and it still never makes sense. NOTHING connects between finals and quizzes and labs and lectures. Half of the stuff she teaches is wrong as well as the questions on her IMPOSSIBLE quizzes. If you want to flunk out of college, i highly recomend her
This class is very difficult and it is not even  for science majors.  It should not be so hard.  Not good for GPA.  Very difficult. Take another science class if you can

Difficult class, this is for non science majors and should not be so difficult.  If you don't like science, do not take this class. Teacher is very difficult. If you have a choice take another class.  Bad for GPA.

If you are not an education major choosing to take this class to fulfill a science credit, i highly recommend taking another class. this class is a gpa ruiner. almost the entire class failed the midterm and her "redemption qiuz" was impossible. i hate karrie more than any teacher i have had before. DO NOT take this class if you can avoid it!

Ms. G was a Seriously awesome instructor that was very willing to help as long as you are willing to learn. She will grade you based on effort. Lets face it physics is not simple, so the course is tough. In the end she looks more how well you improved over the class, how much you added to discusssion and how well you analyzed your labs.
Terrible teacher she doesnt know how to teach.  Goes way too fast in lectures and her tests are impossible.  I passed because of the labs which the TA's grade.  Wouldn't recommend taking this class.

The instructor was both tedious and ineffective when it came to explaining the material to the class. The instructor regularly made mistakes in class and expected students to be able to solve them correctly on exams. I am skeptical about how well I have been prepared for later courses that rely on the practical skills supposed to have been gained.

I've had Dr. Lee for 3 classes now and he gets better every time. He is an interesting guy to listen to and tries to present the material in a way students can understand. He truly cares about the success of his students and really goes out of the way to help you understand and do well. He's not very organized, assigns homework and exams at random.

She is a really great teacher.  She is extremely nice and really interesting.  She is not one to make class longer than what it needs to be.  She gets to the point and you are usually let out of class early.  Highly recommended.

Adrienne is a very nice person but just makes powerpoints straight from the book. She doesn't seem very engaged in the class. It was an easy class but not much was learned. Let out early almost every class and that is if you have class. She does a good job of covering potentially awkward topics. Overall so-so.
Great teacher. Very laid back and fair to her students. The midterm and final are very straightforward. She is very clear in class.

Adrienne is so cool!! She's really chill, very clear and easy to understand. She's a fair teacher who gives hints and doesn't try to screw her students over. Plus there have been multiple times when she's let us out really early! Take her if she teaches next semester!
The tests he gives are harder than the ones given by the other dynamics professors. Would not recommend. His lectures are short but unhelpful.

Dr. Weber wasn't the greatest teacher, but he wasn't bad. He tried in lectures and while not always being the clearest during those, with the homework and equation sheets he gives you you're generally able to prepare yourself for test fairly adequately. Difficult course. Tests are tougher than homework for sure.

This guy is up there with one of the worst teachers I've ever had. Gets very frustrated very easily. Never works through an entire problem because he expects we all know what we are doing after he does something one time.  On the tests he deliberately gives us hard questions we've never seen before because he says we should understand the concept.
The class was quite tough and straight forward.

He is a very interesting guy…. I had a mix up in my lab and something didn't work out well. Rather than telling me I did it wrong and needed to come back again, he drew it out into a long 45 minute lecture…He is rather rude and not very understanding.
Such a great guy. Super smart, helpful, and cares about students who try. Also an interesting person who can be quite funny!
Great guy if you get to know him.  Will always answer your questions
A terrible lab coordinator.  All previous Chem students will agree.  Avoid at all costs!

Dr. P is great! She cares about her students and genuinely wants all of them to do well. She takes time to connect with each student. She assigns a reasonable amount of work and expects the best. Overall a very kind and reasonable woman.
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring

comment: Dr. P is a great professor! She can be thought of as a tough grader, but she does genuinely care about her students and wants you to learn and improve as a nurse above all else. I haven't thought of her as condescending or rude at all, but you absolutely have to participate and work hard in class to do well. I love Dr. P!

She is an intelligent professor and knowledgeable in her field. However, I felt very disrespected and belittled by her on multiple occasions. She isn't approachable and grades additional assignment critically.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: She tries to be nice but she comes off very rude and mean. She also is a VERY tough grader compared to the other teachers, so she should be your last choice. And if you go talk to her in her office about your grade she just picks on you and offers little help.

She is by far the sweetest lady I've ever met. She always tries to keep the class interesting and students engaged. She is genuinely concerned about her students and is overall just a great person. LOVED HER!
So easy and understanding.  Often pushes back due dates and grades super easy.
He was pretty chill when it came to grading my tests, however some rude comments in person.

Cares about his students a lot. Makes time to meet with you whenever you need it. His lectures can sound a bit weird sometimes, and not make sense, but soon you'll come to understand his way of thinking & get used to the things he says. He likes to let students express themselves through papers & project. Very positive. 4 papersprojects total.

Overall, he is a great professor. He is a tough grader, so if you're looking for an easy A, don't take him. 4 assignments over the entire semester. If you put time in, you're going to do okay. He offers many office hours and is helpful when you go.

Henningsen is a cool dude, but my God this man is a tough grader. He is very helpful to talk to during office hours, and it can't hurt to show interest in your work anyway. His classes are interesting and his lectures are engaging. I found his classes enjoyable, no doubt, but what kills me with this guy is the grading. Very tough to get an A

Prof. Henningsen is one of the coolest guys ive ever met and is by far the best professor I had freshman year, no doubt. No short writes, and he is extremely clear on what is needed for your papers. As long as you don't miss paper structure day, you should be fine. He respects everyones opinion and nothing is forced upon you.

Really interesting teacher that loves English a lot. His prompts are the same as all other 1002 professors, but a little more in depth which makes them difficult. If you love English take him! If you're looking for an easy A, probably not your best choice.

I really liked Henningsen, he was a really chill guy. All he really seems to want is that you show interest in improving your writing skills. No short writes is a huge bonus, and as long as you dont write the paper the night before you'll do fine. Very good with giving feedback, though not always 100% clear at times. Would take again.
He is an interesting professor but a hard grader. Overall, he is a cool guy.
Honestly one of the best teachers I've ever had. He respects students' views instead of forcing them to share his views. Bonus, no short writes!

He constantly uses 'critical thinking' and just confuses the crap out of everyone. Class is really awkward and silent. Attendance is mandatory, papers are confusing, unless of course you like a brand new way of writing papers. I liked English, until this class. Not worth it.
He is a great guy and a good teacher, you may become bored at times during class but he I would advise taking his class.
Very entertaining professor.  Classes go by quickly, he is very helpful.  NO SHORT WRITES! He grades well and is very generous.

Professor Hennigsen is still a PHD student here are marquette university. Classes are very boring, but he takes attendence. 4 papers make up the grade, able to make up 1 paper at the end of semester. Overall, pretty easy if you do the papers exactly as specified. Will look over and help with papers during office hours.

Professor Nettleton is great. Lectures are funny and she has a lot of experience in the advertising/marketing industry. Paper criteria is incredibly clear and all the exam material is on her exam reviews. Friday discussions are a breeze and go by quickly. Easy A in my opinion. Would take her again!
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria--Hilarious

comment: Papers from Nettleton clearly state what she wants, lecture is funny, she really utilizes media with videos time to time that relate to class material and are interesting.

Treat opinions as facts and you'll do well in this class. I tried being 'smart' and taking a indepent viewpoint for an assignment and it didn't bode well. On another assignment I took a more sjw stance and did much better.

Nettleton is honestly so cool. She is disliked by some of her students because she is not afraid to speak her mind and teaches  students what others don't. Her class itself is generally pretty interesting, with some boring lectures here and there.  The tests are easy if you do the study guide/review she gives. Overall would take her again!

The papers are graded by whether you did what it says on the rubric or not rather than any part of your grade relating to the content of your paper which is pointless. Hard graders on the two papers. Test answers are basically given to you. Easy to get an A. An A is a 90. I never read. Some discussions are actually interesting.

Dr. Nettleton overall is a good professor. She has great stories and keeps lectures pretty upbeat. The tests are kind of hard, just have to keep up with the reading for sure. Papers are graded decently hard so just make sure to follow the rubric. But she is a very cool professor

Go to class. Powerpoints are online. Read the book. Tests are the same as the study guides. Papers are easy, follow the rubric. Class can sometimes be boring, but overall interesting. Good teacher, really knows what she is talking about.

Paper grading makes no sense, follow the rubic, rubic, and rubic. Key words must be utilized throughout paper. Don't be late. Tests are very easy, the class is the most boring class you will ever take.

Great professor. Class is easy if you go to class and LISTEN. She almost writes the papers for you with a thorough outline of her expectations. Follow the outline or your grade will suffer, its that simple. She teaches you valuable things about media portrayals, sexism, and privileges. Changed the way I see the world.

Took this to meet my Individual and Social Behavior requirement, turns out College of Arts and Science doesn't accept this credit. This class is an easy A, but isn't meant for those who aren't COMM majors. The class is full of pretentious wannabes. 2 essays, 2 exams, attend your discussion. Boom. Nettleton is cool though.

Dr. Nettleton offers a fresh perspective on media. She's so nice and really helpful. I appreciate her effort in leading class discussions, but sometimes they can be a bit redundant and irrelevant. The exams aren't too bad. The questions are  based off the text book readings. READ IT!
Dr. Nettleton is an awesome woman who is passionate about her job. If you have the chance to take her class, DO IT. She is helpful, fun, inspirational, and interesting.
I like Pamela!!She is so awesome, although her tests are hard and not offer study guide. But the review session is so helpful and follow her rubric you will get an easy AB at your paper:)

Do not take her for media in society though she may be the only one. Her exam should have a study guide and its unfair to quiz on so many material we never talked about in class. If there are other teachers teaching this course, I'd recommend them. Exam was very hard! Gives extra credit though. Not an easy teacher despite these reviews stating so

She is a great teacher and has many great connections in and out of the Milwaukee area.  She brings real life experience to class and makes it more than a class. I have learned a lot from her this past semester. However, it is Marquette and is college, so yes you have to work, study, and pay attention to earn the grade you want!

Worst teacher!! Talks about whatever she feels like talking about that day. Barely anything she goes over in class will be on the test. She tells you to follow her rubric exactly on papers and you will be given a good grade, but when she grades the papers (not the TA), she grades it as if it is a grad student's paper and not a freshman.

Dr. Nettleton is extremely helpful and HILARIOUS. She was hands down the most interesting and entertaining teacher I've had at Marquette. In all honesty the course was almost too easy. There are only two papers , a mid-term, and the final. I received As on both of the papers and I'm an engineer major if that tells you anything. Highly recommended!

Dr. Nettleton's Media in Society class was interesting and enjoyable. She is an easy grader on the 2 papers, and the 2 multiple choice tests are easy (a lot of common sense). This was an excellent class and I learned a lot.

I wish I could take her again! She is incredible. I would take any class from her. I actually had my eyes open to things. Make sure you get a good TA for her class, although they are all good, it might change when some of them leave.

Really easy class. Powerpoints are basically useless, lots of pictures and irrelevant things. She likes to target the majority to prove her points. Discussions are easy. Papers are weighed more than exams. Pay attention the few lectures before the essay's due and read the end notes of the chapters, and you have an A.
INCREDIBLE. She actually makes you think, which lots of other professors never do.  Easy class, but awesome lecturer.

Lecture is extremely useless but attendance is mandatory. Tests are very easy as long as you attend discussion and study her power points. One will take very little notes in lecture and you really don't need to.

The lectures are incredibly boring and useless. Most of the powerpoints are85% pictures, and whenever she says "discussion" it really means her sharing her own views and sparking debate. I don't learn much in this class, and she takes things from the book, but it's hard to know what exactly.
INCREDIBLE. That is the only word that can describe how great of a professor she is. Love her and this class.

By far the best journalism professor in the college! She will prepare you for the real world and does it clearly. The other professors won't prepare you at all, so she can be a little hard, but she picks up the slack from the other profs and then some. You have to take her if you want to be prepared for the real world.

If you have the opportunity to take a course with Dr. Nettleton, you'd be stupid not to do it. She is an extremely nice lady who will go out of her way to help you. She has tons of real world experience in writing (books, magazines, plays, essays, you name it).I had a great experience with her and I can guarantee that you will not be dissapointed.

If you are a finance major this is a real easy class.  If you are taking this for FINA 3001 credit it will be a bit more challenging to become interested and learn the material.  A few projects, two tests were worth 2/3 of overall grade.

Tests are unbelievably hard... You can have a note card, but I didn't feel that helped me much. The homework assignments are pretty easy. He uses the textbook very little, but there's always connect problems. Good in class notes...I just struggle to see the relation between the notes and the exam

Investments can be kind of a tricky class, but Dr. Kulchania teaches it very well. Exams can be kind of tough, but they are fair and he is a very lenient grader. Also allows a notecard for the exams. However, the final exam was much more difficult than the first two, and it felt like 2 hours wasn't enough time for it.
Good man, helpful, effort should equal outcome in his classes.

Manoj is BY FAR the best Finance teacher at Marquette. His tests are very fair and based completely on slides. He is very approachable and extremely nice when you have questions or in Office Hours. This is by far the most highly thought of professor in the Finance Department. Awesome guy!

Extremely fair.  Very helpful, shoot him an email if youre confused about a problem on Aplia and he'll help you out.  Goes over what will be on the tests.  Grades generously-if you do the projects he'll give you 100%, and on tests if you make a simple mistake he will only take off a few points, not penalize you for getting the entire thing wrong
Very helpful, makes sure that you are prepared for the tests.  Explains everything in class, textbook is basically not needed at all.
Dr K is the best professor at Marquette!
Great Professor!  Gives good examples.  Is not fussy and focuses on the important things in chapter. Highly recommend him. Requires fair amount of participation though

Dr. Kulchania is an excellent professor. He said this is his first time teaching at MU but he does a great job. Second exam was TOUGH but the curve made it nice. Highly recommend his course. He knows his stuff and connects chapters well

Dr. Kulchania is very helpful.  I had some issues this semester and he was very understanding.  He connects things well and explains  clearly.  He said he just moved to Marquette and I think he is a great teacher!

Honestly, I am not a fan of spanish class. But seÃ±orita Zuidema is very helpful and i was able to do very well in the class with her help.  Since it is a beginners class, she will explain things in english which is EXTREMELY helpful.  She also comes up with a lot of different ways to memorize grammar rules. Likes corgis a lot. Highly recommended.

She is very helpful, kind, and funny!  She makes learning the language enjoyable with fun games and activities.  She also gives you a heads up before pop quizzes.  I would definitely take another class with her if given the chance.

Srta. Z is a good teacher who kinda made the class fun. The material is what is expected in a Spanish 1 class, but she does not present it in a boring way. Also, she is kinda obsessed with Corgis and fills her power points with pictures of them. I would most definitely love to have her as a professor again.

Dr. Morgan is, so far, my favorite professor at Marquette. He clearly loves what he is doing, and he knows what he is talking about. Great class discussions, interesting material, great professor. I would take another class taught by him in a heartbeat.
Great teacher, highly recommend him. He's passionate, smart, witty, and helpful. A genuine, good guy who cares about his students and what he does. Take him.

My favorite professor thus far at Marquette. He genuinely cares about his students and wants you to do well. Very passionate about what he teaches, don't miss the opportunity to take this class. Make sure you do the readings and participate in class and you will do well.

Professor Morgan is a great teacher and an even better person. Incredibly knowledgeable and very passionate. Only downside is if you don't do the assigned readings you're pretty lost in lecture. All the tests have study guides, and for the most part if you pay attention you'll do well.

Professor Morgan is the man. He is passionate about what he does and makes everything clear during his lectures. You get a study guide for each of the three tests which aren't very hard if you study. Also there is a little sports talk at the beginning of monday classes. Awesome teacher. Take him!

He is the best teacher I have had here. I never really liked theo but I actually enjoyed going to class because his passion for his work really showed and made class interesting. Also he doesn't assign too much homework, it's very manageable.

I highly reccomend taking Mr. Morgan.  I feel like I was one of the only people at Marquette that came from all public schools.  I therefore had no clue what theology even was before I came here.  He made things so clear, and unlike other professors he didn't assign huge loads of readings- just small ones that you could easily comprehend.
Super nice Professor who designs his course around interesting, relevant topics

Professor Monson is the best English teacher I've ever had! His classes are engaging. I never thought I was very good at writing but he has given nearly perfect scores on all my papers. He is a SUPER easy grader in my opinion. I'm not an English major so I have appreciated this as a GPA booster. This class wasn't a lot of work either. I recommend.

Tyler is the best English teacher I've ever had. He is very clear about what he expects from you and welcomes questions. If at any time you are unsure of something, feel free to ask or go into his office hours. He's a very interesting person and makes class interesting as a result. Make sure to pay attention in class, but that isn't very hard.

He was by far the best English teacher I have ever had! He is super helpful and welcome to any questions you have about anything. I am in his office at least once a week with a question and he is always super welcoming, I never feel like I don't have his full attention. Lectures are super engaging and you actually want to participate! Take him!!!!!
Loved this class.  He's super nice and extremely friendly plus I learned a lot in his class! Take him if you can!!
Tyler was a great teacher and on top of that an all around great person. He made this class enjoyable
He is a good teacher and is so sweet. Does not pressure people to participate in class. The class has a calm atmosphere and he is not a terrible grader.
Mr. Monson is a good, young teacher. He is polite, engaging, encourages students, and gives positive feedback. I would definitely recommend him as a teacher.
This young prof is great! Classes are always interesting and attending class isn't hard because he is quite easy to look at (: He is fun and makes class engaging! Definately recommend!

Terrible director. He chooses the worst songs and repeats them incessantly. He practices the easy pieces for hours (literally) and we barely look at the hard ones. He's constantly nitpicking over everything and never shows appreciation for our progress. Don't take him. It's not worth it at all.
Made this required course a relatively enjoyable way to spend M/W/F mornings.
Even though i'm an Accounting major, I took this course as an elective- Ms. Z made Amer. Lit. one of my favorite English classes i've had so far :)

Will graduate in December, took this instructor for 2 semesters. Way more sincere than other instructors I have had and she was not into the whole "we are Marquette" thing. i never really liked any English classes before,  but she made American lit. awesome!

I had this instructor for two semesters and she was one of the most understanding I have had at Marquette. Some students took advantage of this at times, asking for extra time to complete papers or working on other assignments during class.
Loved Ms. Paxton, she really cares about her students and won't penalize you for mistakes, but she will help you. Really nice and down to earth, highly recommend.

this teacher is really nice. She is strict but more importantly she makes sure you do your stuff. She is also an extremely hot teacher. makes english class something worth going to. has some HUGE ....
Horrible teacher, thinks she is all that and grades too strict. DO NOT TAKE HER. Her comments on papers do not explain why you received the grade you got.
Even though she is always available for help, it is almost impossible to satisfy what she wants on each paper. If you are very good at writing papers take her, otherwise find someone else.

I had him for Ethics at the University of Akron and he is an amazing professor. He genuinely cares about his students and is passionate about his class. As long as you go to class and take notes you'll pass.

I had him for Intro to Ethics and thought I was going to dread the class; however, i thoroughly enjoyed it. Great guy! He really takes the time to explain things and he makes it relevant to our lives.

Simply put, Blackerby is the man. He makes philosophy very interesting and is extremely helpful and engaging during lecture. He does a good job of challenging students to think deeper on the subject material. If you're hoping to coast through a class and get an A, don't pick him. If you want to grow intellectually, take him.

The best teacher I have had thus far. Spend literally hours with him discussing my paper. He is very accommodating and will basically tell you what to write in your papers if you take the time to go see him. Lectures are exciting and he is extremely enthusiastic about what he is teaching.He will sometimes get frustrated if people don't participate

Great guy, really good discussions. 4 papers with 4 different prompts to choose for each. Just the right amount of work with study. No EC but if visit office hours with your paper you basically get EC.

The class is great. He has his own texts so you don't have to buy the books. His grade consists of 4 papers and a few short assignments and attendance/participation. His lectures really help you understand the subject. I had tried to take this class with another professor and it just didn't work. If you hate phil, this is your guy.

Professor Reid is an obviously kind and caring woman who truly tries to make her class fun and engaging. I suspect her failing in this matter is not due to a lack of trying, but rather the content of the course itself. The work is complete busywork and 95% of the class doesn' even attempt it. Nice person, bad class,0/10 would not take course again

Jen Reid is a horrible teacher all of her class is busy work. She is not an actual teacher just someone that Marquette dumped into a freshman class. She constantly forces you to do absurd in class discussions and has no clear rubric for any of her essays.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--So many papers

comment: Great teacher! I strongly reccommend her!
Prof Keller is a really good professor. Make sure you go to class and follow his comments and you'll do well in class.

Mr. Keller is a pretty cool guy. Class is rarely super boring and he tells you exactly what he wants for the unit papers. Going to office hours for papers is a good idea. It helped me when writing the papers. Plus he really likes the students who put in the extra time and effort to come and talk to him about their papers.

Mr. Keller is a really cool guy. His readings/short writes help a ton when you have to write the unit paper. He made me such a better writer and gives constructive criticism. Overall my favorite english teacher that I have had.
He is a really funny guy and wants everyone to do well in the class, but he takes attendance so make sure you go to class. Always available for help. He's kind of annoying sometimes, but I liked him.
Mr. Keller is a funny, great professor. He really tries to do what he can to help you and your paper get better. He wants to help you do good and he grades fairly.

He's a really good teacher and is super funny. He is a little tough with grading essay's which is mostly what the entire class is about. His class is very fun. He expects everyone to be in class. It is an easy class if essays are good. Overall a fun class.

Her class is really easy! Her lectures are pretty much all discussions and doesn't help very much, but she takes attendence, so attendence is mandatory. She posts everything we need to do online, and its pretty specific. As long as you follow directions, it's easy.

Outstanding teacher. He was my first professor at Marquette: 8am on MWF, and I fell in love with learning. After my first week, I changed my major to Philosophy. He pushes you to think differently, but you will get so much out of this class. Very sad to see him leave Marquette!

I waited to take ethics until my last year, and I am glad that I did.  Matt is great.  Many of the class moments stick with me.  If you want a sluff class, this is not the one.  The papers were tough, and I didn't get as high grades as I would have liked.  Still the class was excellent and I would take it again.  One of my best MU experiences.
Great class.  Great teacher.
This was by far the best academic experience I have had at Marquette, and I am glad that I got prof. Nowachek.
Nice teacher, unclear about expectations in papers. Doesn't help students who need assistance with papers.  Hard Grader, grades given out without explanations.
good.  Papers were hard at times, but he gives alot of help.

I was not too excited about this class at first because I struggled in human nature.  But prof. nowachek made the class worth it.  the class discussions and thought experiments were really interesting.  worth taking.  I would take him

I was not too excited about this class at first because I struggled in human nature.  But prof. nowachek made the class worth it.  the class discussions and thought experiments were really interesting.  worth taking.  I would take him again.
Good teaching, funny, and challenging.
Good class.  Much better than human nature.
Great class.  Hard grader, but I learned alot.  Definitely one of the best classes I have taken at MU.  Will take him again if I can.
Take this class!  Matt is a pasionate teacher who makes the material come alive.  But the readings were difficult at times.  We pretty much covered everything in class, so that was OK.
Awesome class.  The final exam was a bit of a beast, but he gives you all the quesetions 8 weeks before so you have time to study.  The roleplaying was great.

We had class on MWF and the first two days of the week were heavy on reading.  But on Fridays we only did case studies.  I literally prepared for 10 minutes on Thursday nights and then we discussed and debated the issue in class.  Interesting cases.  The teacher was always available in office hours to talk about responses and papers.
This is a really good class.  There is a lot of writing, which you can handle if you like to write.  I like writing, so it was manageable.  He gives pretty good help if you ask.

The first week was great but everything after that was horrible. He has unrealistic expectations of his students and requires far too much written work that you will never receive an A on. Does not offer any guidance for assignments and the only comment he ever leaves you is "Explain." Overall just very arrogant, dramatic, and deceptive.
This was the best philosophy class i have had at mu.  ethics was really interesting.
Great class.  Great professor.

Awful. Pretentious and not helpful at all. You need to go to his office hours frequently in order to get AB's on his assignments. A's are impossible. So much busy work. Complained about not wanting students to regurgitate information back at him, but it is the only way to get any type of good grade. Really upset because I wanted to enjoy this class
this guy is the best. marquette needs more instructors like him
BEST EVER. Such an interesting class. Take it.

Matt is really a great teacher. He has an infectious interest in philosophy that starts to rub off on students by the end of the class, and he is extremely approachable and engaging in class. Readings are pretty much explained in class so you don't really have to read, but it helps especially with papers and exams.

Professor Samuels is incredibly pretentious and very neglecting of other peoples opinions. He corrects the Bible many times in class. His tests are pretty easy but incredibly intricate. He lets you use your notes for them but you better take kick ass notes. He's incredibly frustrating, definitely recommend avoiding him if its at all possible.

He is very intelligent but his class is unconventional. You take notes all period and use these notes in the open note tests. He tests on vocab and terms but not on context. This can make the class very easy or difficult. Once you understand his system it is easy. He is generally interesting to listen to. I love when he says "God" in a dramatic way

This guy is a genius when it comes to theology.  This being said, he is not a good teacher.  He is very vague in discussions and expects his students to know exactly what he is talking about.  He has very specific guidelines that most students can not live up to..

Mr. Samuel is one of the hardest teachers I have ever had.  Yes he is very smart and informative but the tests are impossible.  The class average is always extremely low even though they are open note.  When you ask for feedback he is not that helpful.  I recommend not taking this class if you want to get a good grade in theology.

The tests are all online and the questions are straight from class notes. The readings he gives aren't too time consuming and he goes over them in class. No quizzes or tests in class, just a midterm and final essay. The final one is long but he grades easy. Show up to class and participate and you should get an A.

He gives you readings for homework but then goes over the reading with his notes in class. All his tests are online so if you take notes in class, the questions are directly from his lecture. There are no tests/quizzes in class and there is no midterm or final. Only a midterm paper and final paper which are not bad since he grades kinda easy.

class is made up of two papers, a midterm and final, and one or two group projects. Tests are very hard even if you keep up with the reading and go to class, fairly interesting in class but one has to want to learn about Theology.

Two papers and two tests. The Midterm was extremely difficult and very few people did well. The first paper is a group paper that needs to be ten pages, then the second paper is individual and it also has to be ten pages. I would avoid his class if possible it is a lot of work for very little reward.
His class is very manigable if you do not mind putting forth a lot of effort.  His papers a hassle, being biblical exegesis's, they take a lot of time.

Do not take unless you are a Theology major. His class is not a blow off class like it is supposed to be. His papers are kind of a pain because they are on Biiblical Exegesis. Also, his tests are hard because you have put in order a list of biblical event and remember pointless information such as matching specific psalms to their type. Avoid him.

How anyone can actually like this guy as a teacher? I have no idea. I'm sure he is a nice guy and all outside of class, but he makes you do exegesis which NOBODY else has to do and it is probably the worst thing ever. tests are extremely difficult, he was proud that the class average of his midterm was in the low 60s, which makes no sense. AVOID.

Really annoying.  He did his best to try and help us, but his tests were really hard.  Lots of reading (but that's going to be in every Theo class).  Very helpful with the papers. I felt really helpless in class and he didn't seem to give a lot of insight when you asked him questions. Bearable, but if you can find someone else, do so.

Her lectures are mind numbingly boring. She talks in a very low tone, as if talking to herself and expects us to stay focused the entire hour. Her tests are okay, but she wants you to know specific details. She thinks her class is the only one we have. Avoid this professor.

She seems to think her class is the only class students are taking. The amount of reading required for each class period is insane, and don't think the amount is lowered if you have a paper due in class that same day. Also, her staring grade for papers begins at a C, and that's if you did everything required; she grades as if she's an english prof!

I took his Community Planning course.  He is very disorganized - i.e. he made a major overhaul to the course schedule about halfway through the course.  Exams are pretty easy, but he is very picky with the group paper (group papers are enough of a pain in the ass as it is)  This is a side job for him, and it seems as though he's in over his head.

He makes funny faces when he talks, but he wants everyone to do well and he really helps with any questions you have. His exams are straightforward and he tells you exactly what you need to know in review sessions.

First year teacher who tries really hard to have a good class but is not cut out to be a college professor. His grades range from AB to C on essays, which can be a good or bad thing. Don't expect to learn. Can be sorta interesting with his weird habits. Not a good teacher, but a lot better than other english professors

Dr. Suh was a very caring professor, was always willing to help outside of class, and truly tried to learn and care about her students. The class material itself was very difficult, which meant the exams were difficult. Lecture heavy, which was nice because you didn't have to bring the book to class. Assignments for every class.
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: You will never want to take her international accounting! very poor skill. very bad English to explain herself in this course. Making mistakes all the time and telling us the last lecture was wrong???!!! Her intermediate accounting was fine though.

If you are a senior looking for an easy elective, do not take this (take international tax). Weekly cases that require hours worth of preparation. She also has almost weekly quizzes which are worth extra credit (points add up). Tests are difficult but if you know the study exam you can get an 85% easy. She tries to complicate cases, don't overthink

Dr. Suh made this Accounting course much better than it could have been. She is extremely knowledgeable and helpful in clarifying any questions, and will do whatever she can to help you excel in the class. Accounting can be a dry subject, but Dr. Suh made it infinitely more enjoyable.

Ikeson Suh is one of the best accounting professors I have had. She actually cares about her students and tries to make sure everyone understands the material. If you want to learn accounting take any of her classes.

She has a slight accent and for students who have issues with that, maybe her teaching is unclear. I thought she made accounting interesting and fun and would recommend her as a professor again. Her office hours really help with clarifying the accounting process and she gives practice exams that a reflective of her actual exams.

I would not advise my worst enemy to take this class. The case studies are awful, and does not have to do with what we learn in class. Her mid-term was fine but then all of the sudden the final was everything we had not learned. I had an A in the class and I may possibly have to retake after the final. Worst professor in college.

Extremely difficult professor. Standard homework everyday.  Her exams are not straightforward.  She manages to find the things you don't study to put on the exams.  Most difficult class I have ever taken, many students had to retake it.  She is willing to help if you attend her office hours though.
THE BEST TEACHER IN MARQUETTE!YOU CAN GET AN EASY A EVEN THOUGH YOU ARE A FOREIGNER

Super nice and understanding.  She understands that most students only take the class because we are required to but she makes it very interesting. only grades in class is for online discussions, 1 paper, and one exam.  Defiantly recommend

Megababe.  Haha  It was a pretty easy class.  There was one essay paper due for the midterm grade and then the final exam. The only other grades for that class were for in-class discussions. Classes were almost exclusively discussion on philosophical ideas. It's a lot of fun if you like philosophy. The final was easy enough as long as you study.

If you struggle with writing don't take him. Each week we did a writing interaction, which involved doing short essay responses to the same 5 questions. The big papers are long but not that hard. I never read or paid attention, but I'm a decent writer and found it an easy A. There were no quizzes/tests/midterm/final. No books, so you'll save money.

Only take this class if phil comes easy to you, he is terrible at explaining the concepts! you have a quiz everyday, several big tests, two papers due, and a final. Anderson is not a good teacher for you if phil isn't your thing.

Senor Cortes seemed very passionate about his work and taught the class in an inspiring fasion. The readings were a little tough for me but LUIS (not Louis), answered all my questions for me. Also very easy to get a hold of if you need help.
Extremely knowledgeable and helpful outside of class. 8 page minimum research term paper sucks. Does provide extra credit however. Most boring lectures ever and attendance is graded.
Class is really boring! He goes on and on. Very few grades and a giant term paper at the end! Go to office hours if you have him he will raise any grade just for showing up.

Prof Burns is so nice. He seems kinda weird at first but he is actually pretty funny. Very intelligent but he wants you to do well and he will help you with anything you have questions on. Very understanding, I would recommend him.

super nice, dry yes.. funny yes.. i liked him alot, my favorite teacher of the semester.  very helpful, extremely helpful, extended the time to turn in papers over the weekend.. he gave all the questions for the exams, and not like 100 q's and then only uses 30, he gave like 12 q's and uses 8 of them.  usually short readings for h/w take him!
Terribly boring professor! He read all his lecture notes and he was very dry! I recommend someone else. Class was Hebrew Scriptures
Lots of reading

Dr. Isaac, simply put, is an amazing man. He is thoughtful, and it is clear that he has undergone several life experiences that have shaped his character. That being said, his class was a bit difficult, but Phil of Language is implied to be hard. Terms that were used in lectures could be ambiguous, but very thought-provoking. I enjoyed the class

Professor Isaac is nice and funny, but the word for word memorization of vocab terms can be tough, as can the fact that if class isn't going the way he wants then no review which is an issue when you have to memorize. He can get off topic and fail to cover material in class, and sometimes his explanations feel a touch heavy for an into phil.

This guy seems really cool the first few days but you have to memorize everything verbatim... seriously if you mix up two words you'll get it wrong. The readings are boring and long and you must read to do well. Mid-term is really tough average was about a 50%. I am a serious student that goes to class & studies. GET OUT ASAP had to withdrawal .

Awesome guy, he had people bring in coffee and snacks every day. Has really thought-provoking lectures, however, he is not clear at all. Our class was told what to study for our midterm, and maybe 20% of what he told us was on the midterm. The class average for the midterm was probably around 50%-60%
He's a really cool dude and his class is really engaging. There are quizzes that aren't so bad, however, the midterm was pretty hard. DO THE READINGS, (there's no text book so that's nice)

Brilliant and engaging. Really cares about everyone being able to speak up in class and even works to resolve conflict with opinions arising from philosophical differences. Takes the time to share his life/experiences.

Walter Isaac is a condescending lazy professor. His class lectures consist of him assigning meaningless class debates and student presentations. He never teaches any material and leaves it to unqualified students to teach. When it comes time for grades, he provides 0 feedback and even outright refuses to tell you your grade on debates/presentations

Walter seems to think he's a genius camp councilor encouraging 13 year olds to act like adults; while he's actually of mid-range intelligence, with sleazy confidence and self-assurance. Despicably condescending in every fashion. His class was a obnoxiously contradictory and a complete waste of time that I would never wish on anybody.

I loved his class. I havd Phil of Ed and normally have hated all other Phil courses. Her keeps the class super interesting and is really open to discussion and opinions. He is more interested in you understanding the material enough to apply it to your future, rather than just knowing it for a test. I would totally recommend taking him to everyone.

Interesting and a nice guy, but one of my most least favorite classes. he has his own unique way of grading papers and it's complete crap. Maybe I'm just dumb, but I couldn't understand really anything he was saying/connecting in this class
He was really nice at times, but his grading scale and limited assignments did not work in the favor of the students. I do not recommend him.
He was really nice at times, but his grading scale and limited assignments just didn't work to the benefit of the student. Dont take him
he said class is mandatory, but its really not. I don't recommend taking him.

Thought he would be really good/easy from friends & previous reviews on this site, but he was totally different from his 1st year I guess. Never clear on instructions. NEVER. Rarely answers emails & is hard to get a hold of.Midterm & final are ok.Any other teacher is an easy A. He isn't worth it. Try someone else,this guy is just one big headache.
Best professor I've had at MU. He made me love philosophy. Very personable, unique lectures/discussions, wonderful story teller and really excited to get to know his students.

Probably my #1 favorite teacher at Marquette.  Great guy, very personable, highly inspirational.  Required relatively short readings, accompanied by easy tests (primarily vocab) and in-depth, flexible essays that really made you think out certain philosophies you read about.  Awesome grading system, too!
A very charismatic professor who seeks to push the boundaries of his students thoughts. Does not shy from controversial topics. Very good story teller. Cares about the world and his work.
Keeps the readings short and always discusses them in class.  No quizzes.  Two long papers due right before the midterm and final but the tests are all id terms he gives.

Dr. Evans's class is engaging and consists of lectures and group discussions. She draws on some of her own experiences as a teacher, and she capitalizes on social justice, appropriate for a Jesuit university. Office hours really helped me to make sense of material and even to make sense of experiences I had in my service learning classroom.
Dr. Evans class is not a class that you can just show up and get an A. She is very helpful during her office hours and really cares about her students.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Graded by few things

comment: Dr. Evans is cool in the way she can relate to students. She always lets class out early and understands the difficulties that you have to balance. Her tests are really hard, even when you study it is difficult to get an A. I would recommend taking her, just be ready to study and be engaged in class.

I cannot say enough great things about Karen. I switched into education second semester and I can say wholeheartedly that she really helped reaffirm my decision to switch. Her lectures are amazing--she always has really great anecdotes. Her tests are a little hard in that you have to know more than the definition of a term to pass. Great person!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: She's incredible, you would be lucky to have her. If you can't figure out the extensive help she gives, not doing well is your problem.

Dr. Evans' class was really helpful. I learned a lot and will definitely be using it in the future. You can tell she loves what she does and really cares about you. My only complaint is that she gives an incredible amount of work that she expects you to do in a short amount of time like her class is the only one you're taking. Just prioritize!

She is a good teacher.  The binder she made and has you buy for the Middle School Reading is SO useful!  I will definitely be using that when I am a teacher.  She is really nice and expects a lot from her students.  Very personable.
Terrible, She is easy but you wont learn anything

Had her for CHEM 1001 and 1002. Very helpful to print our her powerpoints and take notes on them in class. Will do a lot of practice problems. Offers a ton of practice quizzes and tests before exams. As long as you do the computer exercises and practice materials you'll do fine.
She was very helpful and I personally enjoyed her dry humor. I took her for two semesters and I have no regrets

I took Dr. Miller's class for CHEM 1001 and then chose to take her class again for CHEM 1002. Her notes/lecture are very straight forward as well as her tests. While the content may be complicated at times, but she is more than willing to meet with you to explain. The worst part of this class is chem lab, but that's not her fault.

Dr. Miller is an excellent teacher.  Her notes are are extremely helpful and they go straight with the book. While her lectures are boring, she explains things pretty well most of the time.  She curves her test a ton and its pretty easy to get a decent grade.  Take her if you can!!!!!!

Dr. Miller gives very similar questions online to prepare for the tests. Discussion questions are also very helpful to study from. The class was not difficult, but tests can be tricky. The hardest part of this class for me was the lab portion.
Very good teacher.  Recomend!! Tests are not impossible.
I did not have AP Chem prior to taking her. She is an excellent teacher who has great powerpoints and has realistic expectations. I would take her again forsure if given the choice.

She is a FANTASTIC teacher...Take her class! Tests are very lecture heavy...book is only used for extra clarification. She provides her powerpoints online which is very helpful, print them out and use for notes. Great Professor!

Diane Miller. Beautiful. Stunning. Intelligent. Beautiful. She's extremely helpful when you approach her and is dedicated to her students. She is quite shy and can be quiet in lectures, but soon into the course you'll find this to be her most attractive trait. The way she works her clicker is enough to make anyone fall in love. Take her.
She's the best! easiest professor for chem1, she curves ALOT!! exams grades D,D,D,D,F final grade C!
Pretty good professor. Goes through powerpoints in class; if you study them and do the ARIS practice problems online, you should do fairly well.

Boring. I skipped most of my lectures due to this. Her ppts are directly from the book, and she posts only part of them online - leaving the key things off. Her tests are directly from the ppts/discussion worksheets/aris though, so they were very straightforward and easy.

Pretty good teacher. Her tests are straight from her notes and discussion questions.She can be pretty funny sometimes. Also, she is very helpful and truly cares about how her students are doing in her class.
good

Dr Miller is a wonderful professor! She can be confusing in lectures sometimes because she goes through her notes very quickly. but she is very helpful! She clearly loves her job and is extrememly friendly and helpful to students who ask for extra help. I definintly reccommend her!

Lecture can be very boring. She goes through powerpoints that are very dull and you have to take notes because she doesn't put them online.  If you study THE CONCEPTS and her slides thoroughly you'll do ok on the test. Decent curve on each test just like other chem classes. Try to take "Yi" if possible for Chem 1002, if not this is decent #2 choice

I took PHIL 1001 with Dr. Mott over the summer, and it was his last semester at Marquette University.  Grade is 3 exams, each 30%, and attendance, 10%. The day before each exam, he had 2 groups each write 16 test questions and answer them.  Then, for the test, he selected questions from those reviews and told us the essay question! Easy-I got 100%.

Dr. Mott is an expert in philosophy. It is a hard subject, especially at the 1001 level because it challenges the way you think. However, he has excellent explanation technique and I felt comfortable asking questions and asking for help privately.

Dr. Mott grades fairly based on 3 long essays and a presentation. Class was taught by students for close to 2 months via presentation, so if you're paying money for a professor to teach, this probably isn't for you. If you're into self teaching and relying on your peers to do their work and educate you, all aboard.

Dr. Mott is very intelligent, and a great professor. The people saying he's bad are honestly just lazy. You never have to do a single reading, just go to class and take good notes. He does such a good job explaining the readings, and that's all you need. Plus he's an awesome guy.

DO NOT TAKE! I really did not like his sarcastic comments every class. He is not a good professor. He stands in front of the room for 90-95% of the time and is not easy to understand. He was not a good professor and I would recommend not taking him!

Really really nice guy. He lets you choose your own questions for his tests, and if you go into his office hours he'll tell you what the essay question will be. He's chill and easy to talk to. Highly recommend!

90% of class was 3 exams and 10% was attendance. Overall really easy class, Dr.Mott is intelligent with good, objective responses, promotes debate, and is usually pretty clear. Every exam has questions from study guides we make in class! It seemed boring at first but around midsemester things got interesting

Professor Mott holds boring lectures in which he stands at the front of the classroom for 80-90% of class time talking without pause.  He now determines grades through three open ended essay based examinations.  There is no study guide, everything concerning the class is vague and subjective.

Only 3 papers and participation for grade. Grading on papers is fair, and he offers to look over the papers prior to one week before due date. Topics of papers were not that interesting. Lectures for 90% of time, but lectures are interesting. Cool guy, would take again.

great teacher. honestly the readings are difficult but explains the entire reading in class. He explains everything by voice no power points but just listen and come to class. dont even have to read text b/c he explains everything. his test are based off of his notes easy A if you take good notes and come to class

Horrible teacher! Speeds through his notes and his students sit dumbfounded because they can't understand half of what he is saying, because he just reads, and reads, from his outline without ever taking a break/explaining. Tests are near impossible, reading is necessary if you want a good grade on the tests. Good Luck! You will need it!
Does not take attendance! Lectures the whole class but is very interesting and has great examples.
no tests, 3 papers, not my favorite, lots of class discussion

Mark Trump is an awesome professor, he challenges peoples views on theology without ever pushing his own view on you.  Everything he talks about has a biblical reference.  I loved him so much I took him twice and got an A both times!!

Awesome professor, very interesting. Keeps your attention with funny/quirky lines and stories that usually have some relevance to the notes. Very helpful when something is confusing. Uses two texts besides the bible, Politics of Jesus (9780802807342) and Resident Aliens (9780687361595). Buy from the Kindle store, they're cheaper than anywhere else.
Explains readings in class. Engaging and funny. Cancels class somewhat often. 4 1-page papers, a mid-term, and a final. I would definitely recommend him as a professor.

John is a fairly good instructor. He knows the limitations of college students and tailors his class so students can succeed. His general knowledge of philosophy is ridiculous, as well as his entertaining personality. I enjoyed this class alot and he made it interesting. A word of caution though, he missed a ton of classes and is hard to contact.
made his final much more difficult than his previous tests.

it's actually a rather hard class. I don't reccommend taking her. it's basically bible regurgitation and her leading discussions. people should have participated more. but yeah, don't take this if you are looking for an easy class.

Ellen is an interesting lady. She is a modern scholar who likes to show her knowledge condescendingly.  You will learn a lot in the class, but if Theo isn't your cup of tea, I would not recommend this class.  If you don't submit your essay(s) up to her standards/views, then you will not do well. Tests are MC, fill in blank, and essay.
